title: apple crisp
directions: Set oven at 375°.
In a deep 9-inch pie plate, layer apples, lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, sugar, oatmeal, cinnamon and butter.
Mix it with a fork or use your fingers until they're mixed thoroughly. Sprinkle the topping over the apples and bake for 45 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: mini-minnie pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toast the English muffin in a toaster until lightly browned.
Spoon 1/4 of the pizza or spaghetti sauce on each muffin half.
Top each one with Mozzarella cheese.
Place the muffins on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Put the sheet into the oven and cook for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove from the oven.
Let it cool 2 minutes before eating.
Yields 4 pizzas.

title: garden vegetable bake
directions: Layer sliced vegetables in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle oil over top and season with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Should be firm, not mushy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Heat together soup and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper for taste.
Set aside.
Boil together zucchini, carrots and onion until tender; drain and mix together with soup and sour cream.

title: midori melon colada
directions: Mix in blender and serve.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler until smooth.
Add pecans. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper, then chill.
Combine chocolate morsels and shortening in a double boiler until smooth.
Dip caramel morsels in chocolate mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: green pea loaf with carrot sauce
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased loaf pan in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: caramel ice pecans
directions: Cook until you can form a soft ball.
Stir in pecans and drop on wax paper.

title: warm mixed green salad
directions: Blend together all ingredients, with the exception of the lettuce in the microwave-safe bowl for 1 minute.
Place the greens in a bowl; toss with the hot dressing and serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees, in a bundt pan.

title: carrot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, then turn temperature to 350° and bake until it isn't sticky when touched with your finger (about 30 minutes). When cool, put meringue on top and brown.

title: 15 minute zesty chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine egg white and milk.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and seasonings.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture, then in crumb mixture.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides until no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: leslie's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let cream cheese and eggs come to room temperature.
Combine first 4 ingredients and press in the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix on low speed cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off and keep in oven for 2 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: marshmallow fudge candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 5 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients and pour into greased dish.

title: cream cheese banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs.
Stir in Bisquick and nuts; do not beat.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until done, at 350°. Makes 1 large loaf.
Freezes well.

title: fresh brewed mint tea
directions: First Pot:
Bring to boil 4 cups of water.
Steep mint and tea bags in water for 30 minutes.

title: nova scotia blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Sprinkle lemon juice over blueberries, then sprinkle sugar mixture over blueberries; stir gently.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Spoon blueberries into deep dish pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Gently lay other pie shell over the top.
Crimp the edges with a fork.
Slash top crust in a few places to let juice boil out.
Rub crust gently with water, then sprinkle sugar over the top.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Watch it so that the crust will not burn.
Reduce heat if necessary.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: company banana pudding(children's)
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a bowl.
Beat until thickened. Fold in the sour cream and whipped topping.
Make layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture in a serving dish until all ingredients are used.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.

title: plantation corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
This can be doubled.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sweet potatoes to mixture, mixing well. Combine flour and next 7 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, raisins and pecans.
Beat egg whites (room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove; cool completely. Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add all other ingredients. Simmer for
minutes.	Put
in
casserole
dish.
Top with sliced Velveeta
cheese.
Put in oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: fancy cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir in mayonnaise to moisten. Chill.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: fish with cheese and tomato sauce
directions: Sprinkle fish with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes. Combine cheese, sour cream, milk, salt, pepper, parsley and tomato puree and stir into smooth paste.
Arrange one layer of fish in glass pan.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Continue with layers but finish with cheese mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes, covered, in oven at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with butter, bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Return to oven uncovered for another 15 minutes to brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll out.
Melt butter and spread over dough.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Frost, if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, add brown sugar, bring to a boil. Add corn syrup; stirring constantly. Bring to a boil again. Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda, vanilla, salt. Pour over popcorn and mix well. Bake at 250 degrees for one hour. Stir with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.

title: shrimp creole with rice
directions: Saute all chopped vegetables in butter in a large saucepan. Add the canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste and the seasonings. Simmer, stirring often, about 45 minutes. Add the cooked shrimp and simmer 10 minutes more.
Line a large platter with cooked rice and pile shrimp creole in center.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: party crackers
directions: Put crackers in round gallon glass jar. Mix all ingredients. Pour into jar. Put lid on and roll and roll and roll until mixture is seeped into crackers.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar and cocoa together in 2-quart glass bowl.
Place margarine on top and pour evaporated milk over this, without stirring.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High heat to soften the margarine.
Add the vanilla.
Whip smooth with a wooden spoon. Line an 8-inch square pan with plastic wrap and pour in mixture. Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Layer in casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.
While this is browning, add all other ingredients in a thick cooker and bring to a boil. Mix browned sugar and let it all cook together 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until ready to put on cake.
(Good on yellow or spice cake.)
I add black walnuts to my icing.

title: virtuous cheesecake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients with hand mixer on medium speed. Mix in sour cream and egg whites.
Spray a pie pan with nonfat cooking spray and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cheesecake mixture into pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and serve with sliced strawberries or desired sliced fruit.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix the flour,
salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add the milk and mix into
a smooth batter.
Add the melted butter and the eggs; whip into a
smooth batter.
Cook on a grill or in a large nonstick frypan.

title: pork-vegetable stir-fry
directions: Mix well the soy sauce, chicken
broth, sugar and cornstarch; set aside.
In a large skillet or wok, heat oil.
Add pork; cook and stir quickly until just tender.
Add onions, celery and carrots.
Stir over high heat 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in bean sprouts.
Stir soy mixture; add to vegetable-pork mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Crumble Doritos and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. (Reserve some for topping.)
Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine beef, soups, Ro-Tel and chili beans.
Pour over Doritos.
Top with remaining Doritos.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Mix sugar and flour; add juice and mix well.
Stir in pineapple and cheese. Mix well.
Pour in 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix butter and crushed crackers; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour pecans, then beat until creamy.

title: grandma's crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening, brown sugar and 1 cup white sugar thoroughly.
Remove 1 cup and reserve for crumb topping.
To the rest, add eggs and spices.
Stir soda into sour milk and add to cake mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cake batter into pan.
Crumble topping over. Sprinkle chocolate chips over topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat juice and water; dissolve jello. Melt cream cheese by adding hot jello a little at a time, and stirring well with a fork.
Add cream which has been whipped, pineapple and pecans.

title: baking mix banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add baking mix, being careful not to overmix.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 55 to 65 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: summer squash tomato casserole
directions: Place squash slices in a casserole dish.
Cover with tomato slices and onions.
Sprinkle with the next four ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Bread pan size 9 3/4 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch makes 1 loaf.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls
directions: Place bread balls into a buttered Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with box of pudding mix.
Melt together butter and brown sugar. Drizzle over top.
Saran Wrap tight and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no oil spicy salad dressing
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into cooled liquid mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: baked beans and rice
directions: Pour beans and tomatoes into pot and begin to heat. Meantime, saute onions and garlic in olive oil in skillet.
When limp, add to beans and simmer until flavor is good enough to eat.
Serve over rice.

title: purple passion pie
directions: Beat Dream Whip, milk and cream cheese together.
Fold in pie filling.
Pour into crust.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salt and pepper until tender.
Drain and cut into cubes.
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream well.
Spread in greased 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Crush ritz crackers over top of mixture.
Then pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Easy and delicious anytime.
Goes good over cooked rice.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight fitting lid.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Refrigerate up to 2 weeks.
Shake before using.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Enough for 3 meals.

title: strawberry avocado salad
directions: Blend sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard and onion powder. Gradually add oil and blend.
Stir in poppy seed.
In a salad bowl, combine salad greens, avocados and strawberries.
Before serving, drizzle with dressing and toss.

title: sweet apple bread
directions: Blend all ingredients in bowl; pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Test with toothpick.

title: tuna casserole
directions: You will need one large casserole dish or an oblong pan.
Use extra according to amount and taste.
This recipe is for four.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until ground beef is cooked thoroughly; drain and cool.
Keep beef refrigerated until salad is assembled.
Chop lettuce and dice tomatoes.
Drain kidney beans. Assemble salad immediately before serving.
Break corn chips into bite size pieces.
In following order, layer beef-onion mix, beans, lettuce, tomatoes, corn chips and cheese in single layers.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder (or less, if desired) on each meat layer.
Pour Italian dressing on top of layers.
Mix salad and serve immediately.

title: puffy german feast
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Heat 1/2 inch oil in skillet. Dip slices of bread into batter and fry on both sides until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or put syrup on it.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Boil in unsalted water until soft. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Place in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 375 until light brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayo, onion, egg, salt and pepper together.
Then add squash.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese and margarine.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Fry sausage all cut up.
Mix together the Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
To assemble lasagna, spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch deep baking dish.
Pour 1 1/3 cups of sauce in bottom; add a layer of lasagna strips.
Sprinkle some of the cheeses and sausage.
Add another layer of lasagna strips.
Repeat layers, ending with 1 1/3 cups of sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and sausage on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top to taste. Bake covered with aluminum foil in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8. Serve with tossed salad and French bread.

title: german apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat in an ovenproof skillet (cast-iron works great).
Saute apples until just tender.
Remove apples from pan.
Put empty pan in oven while making batter.
The pan must be hot for recipe to work.

title: decorator icing
directions: Cream together the white and butter flavor vanilla, meringue and Crisco. Beat at high speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sugar gradually. Beat and add more sugar. Add water (milk). Add the rest of the sugar and blend on high for at least 5 to 6 minutes. If too thick, add more water (milk).
Don't make too thin or you can't make the designs for your cake.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Steam whole zucchini 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Cool slightly; slice lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp and set pulp and shells aside.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in an 8-cup microwave container.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add soda to mixture.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Microwave popcorn mixture on High for 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.

title: australian pikelets
directions: Mix real good.
Fry in electric skillet in very little grease to look like a small pancake (about the size of a jar lid). Spread jelly on them or eat alone.
These are made for afternoon teas in Australia.
Makes good snacks hot or cold.

title: chocolate marshmallow haystacks
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until well blended.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix in chocolate and vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into coconut; roll until well coated. Place on waxed paper-lined tray.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes about four dozen candies.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Slice onions and peppers.
Mix salt with cucumbers, onions and peppers and cover with water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over drained vegetables.
Heat through and through and can.
Seal in glass jars.

title: nanny's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to boiling.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cereal and mix.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat milk and soup.
Add cheese.
Dissolve.
Add rice, broccoli and seasonings.
Pour in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350°, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: miss ione's prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Then combine mixture and add mashed prunes, 1 cup flour and eggs.
Then add remainder of flour, spices and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour and cream.
Melt butter; add flour.
When smoothly blended, add cream and bring to a boil. Add mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine with lobster meat and mushrooms.
Fill individual shells or casserole with mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese and brown under broiler flame.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir with fork or pastry knife the shortening, flour and salt until crumbly.
Add water, starting with 3 tablespoons and adding more if needed.
Split in half and roll two 9-inch crusts for pie.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly with a mixer.
Add condensed milk.
Pour into an ice cream maker can.
Add enough regular milk to fill line and freeze according to ice cream maker's instructions.

title: swedish sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Fold in flour.
Fold in ground pecans.
Wrap dough in a ball in waxed paper.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut dough into quarters and form long rolls approximately 1-inch round.
Cut cookies 1/3-inch thick onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar; store in closed container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and chop.
Save 3 cups of broth.
Mix chopped chicken with rice, soup and broth.
Add celery, onions and mayonnaise.
Mix cereal with melted margarine. Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3 layer dessert
directions: Mix.
Make crust and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased with margarine).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: clam chowder
directions: Brown meat slightly.
Add vegetables and simmer together in butter.
Blend in flour (sprinkle over).
Add clam juice and chicken broth to make 2 quarts.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add half and half, clams and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in medium-cut coconut or crushed peanuts.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized cubes (this takes about two months).
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
Yields about 3800 portions.
If more guests are expected, add the rabbits.
However, add rabbits only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done and chop. Put drained broccoli in bottom of casserole and cover with chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken and broccoli. Cover with cheese, butter and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add milk and sugar and mix well. Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto lightly buttered platter.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix dry dressing, milk and mayonnaise with wire whip.
Use only 1/2 cup of this mixture and add softened cream cheese.
Mix well with fork/whip.
Fold in Cheddar cheese and mix well.
Form balls (1 large or 2 small) and roll in nuts or bacon bits.
(May be frozen.)

title: microwave fudge
directions: Do not stir.
Put in microwave until butter melts.
Stir in a teaspoon of vanilla and nuts. Put in freezer for 15 minutes.

title: lilly salad
directions: Combine fruit and marshmallows. Fold in whipped cream, coconut and pecans.

title: homemade bread
directions: Knead all ingredients until a dent made with your fingers fills quickly.
Let rise until doubles in bulk (about 3 hours). Place in pans.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Bake in 350° oven.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan, blend first 5 ingredients well. Stir in 10 cups water. Cook on medium-high heat and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook an additional 2 minutes. Add lemon juice and, if desired, food coloring. Add the apples to sauce. Stir constantly and bring mixture up to rolling boil. Cook 1 minute at a rolling boil. Keep saucepan on the burner and ladle mixture into sterile jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Process in boiling water bath 25 minutes for pints or quarts.

title: broccoli cauliflower cheese medley
directions: Cook vegetables as directed. In a medium size bowl, melt margarine for 30 seconds in microwave. Add flour, pepper, dill and parsley. Add bouillon and mix with wire whip. It will be a thick paste. Add milk and stir. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir again. Microwave again for 2 minutes. Stir in cheese and microwave again for 1 minute. Sauce should be smooth and medium thick. Pour over vegetables in a casserole dish. Add croutons, 8 tomato wedges and sprinkle with paprika. Reheat in microwave as needed.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and use 2 teaspoons per cup of water.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, melted margarine, sugar, salt, dark syrup and vanilla together.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Pour syrup mixture over the pecans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers and butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour. Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°. Roll about 1/3 of the dough at a time, 1/8 inch thick on floured board. Transfer rounds with spatula to a piece of wax paper that is heavily coated with granulated sugar. Turn each round so that both sides are coated with sugar. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Prick rounds with a fork 3 or 4 times. Bake 7 to 9 minutes. Cool. Put cookies together in pairs with creamy filling.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients on high speed for 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and chocolate bar.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: jack-o-lantern cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Prepare, bake and cool cake, following package directions. Measure 1/4 cup frosting into small bowl.
Tint with green food coloring.
Place ice cream cone upside down on waxed paper.
Frost with green frosting; refrigerate.
Tint remaining frosting with red and yellow food coloring until frosting is desired orange color.
Measure 3 tablespoons orange frosting in small bowl; add green food coloring to make brown frosting.
Frost cake with orange frosting.
Make eyes, mouth and nose with brown frosting as desired on pumpkin.
Place green frosted ice cream cone in center hole for stem.

title: edith's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and stir in butter.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and pasta sicilian
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken, coated and chopped into squares.
At the same time, start cooking pasta as directions on box say.
Toss pasta together with walnuts and margarine.
When chicken is browned, prepare pasta on dish and serve chicken on top.
Pour pasta sauce over dish and garnish with sesame seed and basil.
Serve with Chardonnay.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda over creamed mixture; blend thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake in a moderate oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: "do ahead" mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in a small amount of water until soft.
In a large bowl, cream potatoes with butter and milk until smooth.
Add all other ingredients, shredded cheese last and cream until smooth (mixture will be runny).
Pour into a buttered baking dish. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and no longer runny in the middle.
In a flat baking dish, bake about 40 minutes.
In a taller dish, about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: himmel fritter
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and eggs together.
Stir in dates and walnuts and spread into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan or small cookie sheet.
Bake 50 minutes at 250°.
Cool.
Break in small pieces on large platter or pan.
Mix oranges and 1/2 cup sugar together and let stand 1/2 hour or more.
Add the mixture to the broken pieces.
Top with the bananas and whipped cream. Decorate with maraschino cherries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In large bowl, beat 1 egg slightly and add vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Then mix dry ingredients and add slowly.
Mix well. Pour into ungreased pan and top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and Miracle Whip.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla flavoring and salt.
Bake 1 hour or 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the following together and bring to a boil:
oil, vinegar, tomato soup, sugar, pepper, salt, salad mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
After boiling, let cool.
Layer carrots, then peppers and onions.
Repeat and pour sauce until gone.
Make sure it covers completely.
Let chill overnight.

title: kevin's dip
directions: Saute sausage, hamburger and onion over medium heat until browned. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on simmer or low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: microwave chicken ole
directions: Mix together taco seasoning, salt and garlic powder.
Add chicken to coat.
In shallow glass baking pan, place chicken. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Turn. Uncover and cook 5 minutes.
Place tomatoes, olives, onion and chilies over chicken; pour broth over all.
Cover and microwave, turning once, on High about 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Return to oven for additional cooking if not fork-tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter. Mix cornstarch and water; add to vegetables in dish and microwave for 3 minutes, stirring every minute until thick.
Pour over chicken.
Top with sour cream and chips.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugars, butter and eggs. Add flour, pumpkin, water, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves. Mix thoroughly. Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into 4 greased mini loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tested done.

title: fruity fig loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 2 1/2-inch (6.5 cm) deep loaf pan that is about 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch (23.5 x 13 cm) in size.
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper of exact size.
Butter waxed paper and side of pan.
Mix beaten eggs with sugar.
Add oil and whisk to incorporate.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Add 1/3 to egg batter and beat well.
Repeat for remaining flour.
Stir in figs, rum and pecans.
Pour batter into mold and bake in the middle of oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
When cake is done, remove and let cool slightly before unmolding.
Finish cooling on wire rack.

title: lynn's broiled pork chops
directions: In a mixing bowl mix together the above seasonings. Boil pork chops in water for 10 minutes. Drain and pat dry. Put pork chops in casserole dish. Pour all the ingredients over the pork chops. Put lid on dish and cook on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place on buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish the apples and sprinkle with the salt, cinnamon and water.
Mix the sugar, butter and sifted flour. Drop mixture over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Heat Mexican Meat separately from beans.
On each plate, layer chips, meat, then beans, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese preference to taste.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Peel apples, cut in halves and core.
Roll out biscuits until thin.
Wrap each half in a biscuit.
Place in a baking dish.
In boiler, heat 2 cups water, 2 cups sugar, 1 stick oleo and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 325° to 400° for 45 minutes.
Baste with juice every 15 minutes.

title: italian frosting
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients in pan until thick like mashed potatoes. Whip and chill. Place last 3 ingredients in bowl. Add flour mixture. Beat until smooth. Spreads better when freshly made. Then refrigerate.

title: homemade cream of tomato soup(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Put canned tomatoes, chopped onion, celery seed, sugar, bay leaf and whole clove in saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Make white sauce of butter or margarine, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Force tomato-seasoning mixture through strainer or food mill to make tomato puree.
Stir puree slowly into white sauce and heat for 1/2 minute.
Serve immediately in hot soup bowls and garnish with croutons, parsley flakes or chopped chives.

title: swiss steak(microwave)
directions: Place margarine in 2 quart 12 x 7 glass baking dish. Microwave on ROAST for 1 minute or until melted.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt, pepper in plate.
Coat meat in seasoned flour.
Arrange seasoned meat in melted margarine. Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.

title: pistachio jello dessert
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together, then add other ingredients; chill and serve.

title: memphis corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain immediately and return to pot.
Add olive oil and toss to coat. Stir in evaporated milk, cheese, garlic and basil.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Do not over-cook (or the pasta will absorb the sauce).
The mixture should be creamy.

title: angel's wings (chrust)
directions: Cut butter into the flour; add egg yolks and sour cream mixed with salt and rum.
The dough should not be so wet that it will stick to the floured board.
If too wet, add a little more flour. Beat the dough against the board until bubbles appear, then set aside covered for 30 minutes.
Working with small amount of dough at a time, roll out to a sheet 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into long strips, about 1 inch wide by 4 inches long, cutting end diagonally. Makes a slit 2-inches long in center of each strip and pull end through the slit.

title: cheese wafers
directions: In a food processor or electric mixer, combine all of the ingredients.
Roll into logs; cover and refrigerate until firm. Grease a cookie sheet.
Slice in wafers and place on the cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: cowboy's dog bone treats
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, milk, corn meal, sugar and bouillon.
Add shortening and work until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add egg and water.
Mix well.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in irregular shapes or use cookie cutter.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on Medium-high.
Turn cookies over; microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Cookies will be firm and dry to touch.
As they cool, they will get crisp.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add garlic, tomato sauce and enough water to make about 2 quarts sauce. Simmer for at least an hour.
Strain the meat from sauce.
Make a gravy of the sauce with the cornstarch, not real thick.
Add more water if too thick.

title: baked fiesta spinach dip
directions: Saut the onion in oil in a medium skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add the salsa.
Drain the spinach and squeeze dry. Add the spinach to the skillet.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Stir in 2 cups of the Monterey Jack, the cream cheese, cream and olives.
Sprinkle with the pecans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Monterey Jack.
Serve hot.
Yield:
5 cups.

title: fish chowder 1
directions: Poach fish in some water, vinegar and peppercorns until it flakes.
Remove, drain and flake.
Saute ham or bacon in margarine. Add vegetables and continue until these are softened.
Add milk and soup.
Continue heating while stirring, but do not allow to boil. Add the fish and heat a few more minutes.
May also be served cold.

title: pork sausage enchiladas
directions: Cook and crumble sausage with onion.
Stir in picante sauce and cumin.
Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 5 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Put about 2 teaspoons of meat mixture.
Roll and place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining picante sauce over enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until hot.
Top with guacamole or tomatoes, if desired.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a rolling boil; cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat; quickly add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Let stand about 1/2 hour.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: crock salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add tomato wedges, sliced cucumbers, green pepper and sliced onions.
Will keep keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: heavenly pudding
directions: Combine pineapple and marshmallows.
Let stand overnight.
Add nuts and fold in Cool Whip. Serve.

title: butter tart squares
directions: Combine and mix 2 minutes on medium speed.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease shallow baking dish.
Mix all ingredients, stirring well. Pour into baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers (about 2 handfuls).
Melt 1 stick of butter or oleo and put on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Cover and chill all of the ingredients.
Amounts of mayonnaise, sour cream, etc. can be adjusted so sauce is not soupy!

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine ingredients with electric mixer, adding eggs one at a time.
Add nuts and carrots last.
Pour into baking pan (oblong, angel food or 2 layers).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes for layer or 1 hour and 20 minutes for angel food pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook 5 minutes.
After it starts to boil, stir continuously. Remove from heat, add 1 jar Hip-O-Lite (or any other marshmallow cream) and 1 pint of peanut butter.
Stir until thick; pour immediately into greased pan.
Let cool, then block out.

title: baked breadfruit(ulu)
directions: Place ulu cubes in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices and brown sugar.
Drizzle with melted butter and lemon juice. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Mix zucchini and eggs together, add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Now add the sifted dry ingredients.
Put in two greased loaf pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and put in casserole dish.
Crumble buns over pineapple.
Mix margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Pour this mixture over buns and pineapple.
Let set 30 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar and egg yolks (one at a time).
Add flour, soda, milk and vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Simmer until thickened.
Add rice; spoon into a 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 400°.
Good over rice.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, chocolate syrup, flour and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured cookie pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
While brownies are baking, prepare following frosting.

title: seafoam
directions: Put egg whites into a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Put the next 5 ingredients into a saucepan. Stir thoroughly over medium heat. Cook to hard ball stage.
Do not stir. Remove from heat to cool while beating egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add the syrup, beating thoroughly.
Beating must continue until candy is past the pulling stage and starts to get creamy and holds shape. Add vanilla and nuts (optional) until candy holds swirls.
Quickly drop candy from spoon into mounds on waxed paper.

title: date nut cherry cake
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla in bowl.
In another bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add fruit and nuts into this mixture.
Blend fruit mixture into egg mixture.
Add this mixture to flour mixture.
Grease a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Line pan with brown paper bag and grease it.
Pour batter and spread evenly. Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
If desired, sprinkle with shot of whisky over top of cool cake. Freezes well, wrap in foil to freeze.
Don't put liquor on, if freezing.

title: chili verde
directions: Dice round steak into small cubes.
Put in large pan or skillet with small amount of oil.
Brown this and all the chopped onion.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the green chilies.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes more.
Thicken with cornstarch, if you wish. Use over tortillas, as a filler for burritos, chips, etc.

title: goulash
directions: Cook chicken first.
Take chicken out and cook rice in same pot.
When rice is done, cut all ingredients into small or medium pieces and let it cook until desired doneness.

title: mary's fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk and chocolate together until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool until you can hold your hand on bottom of pan.
Add vanilla (and nuts) and beat until creamy.
Pour onto buttered platters.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix together the caramel topping with the softened cream cheese.
Pare and slice apples just before serving.
Sprinkle a little lemon juice on them to retard the browning of the apples. Makes 24.
Can be made a couple of days ahead.

title: cyndy's shredded barbecue chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and remove skin.
Cut into small pieces and place in large skillet.
Add all ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Keep stirring and adding a little water.
The ingredients listed are to your taste.
You can also use dark meat if you prefer.
The chicken will shred as it simmers and you stir. It's delicious!

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in large pan and store in tightly covered container. One fourth cup per serving.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix honey, mayonnaise and mustard. Chill. Serve on mixed green salad.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix dressing together.
Let set.
Break noodles (do not cook). Mix together with cabbage, sunflower seeds, almonds and onions. Add dressing.
Mix and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sugar, flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon).
Add oleo, eggs and vanilla butternut flavor; add zucchini.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Add all other ingredients. Cook, while stirring, over medium-high heat for 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan. While still warm, knead on counter for 1 minute.
Store in airtight container.
Makes enough for 5 to 6 children.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Clean and remove stems and scoop out small amount of pulp from mushrooms.
Chop stems and pulp. Combine butter, onion and cheese.
Sprinkle salt on mushroom caps.
Stuff with filling; mound up on top.
Place mushrooms in greased baking dish.
Pour cream in bottom.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove mushrooms from cream; keep warm.
Pour cream into saucepan.
Heat until reduced to half.
Add crab meat; spoon over mushrooms.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix milk, butter, cocoa and sugar; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper; let cool.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in greased deep 9-inch square dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Very good with chili beans.

title: bean soup
directions: When beans are done, mash 1 cup beans per pound and return to pan.
Liquid should be soupy.

title: spinach or broccoli souffle
directions: Cook spinach or broccoli a few minutes.
Drain.
Beat egg; add mushroom soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onion; add spinach or broccoli.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in a plastic bag.
Beat milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese and beat until fluffy and creamy. Use 8 or 10 new small flowerpots.
Put 1/3 pudding mix and cookies for 3 layers.
Scatter final layer of cookies to look like dirt.
Place a silk or plastic flower in center of each.
For children, use gummy worms.

title: smoky cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Chill slightly. Shape into balls.
May roll in nuts of some kind.

title: merry cranberry margaritas
directions: Pour 1/4 cup cranberry juice into a shallow bowl.
Pour 3 tablespoons sugar onto a flat plate.
Dip the rims of 4 to 6 wide-mouthed glasses into juice, then into sugar and set aside.

title: wiener bean bake for 30
directions: Day ahead, cook and season dried kidney beans.
Cook just until tender.
Drain.
Refrigerate overnight.
Prepare limas as package directs.
Drain.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine cooked kidney beans, undrained pork and beans and cooked limas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into steam table pan that has been pan sprayed.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover. Stir and return to oven.
Bake additional 1 hour.

title: sausage soup with tortellini
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown sausage meat (out of casing) with chopped onion until brown.
Drain off drippings.
Add beef broth, water, wine, tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil and parsley.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Skim any fat off.
Add carrots and cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 5 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: crunchy cups
directions: Mix
all of the ingredients together except the candied fruit. Spoon
mixture
into
paper
candy cups.
Garnish with pieces of candied cherries and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: provencal grilled lamb chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Marinate chops in marinade and let stand at least 2 hours (ideally overnight or all day in refrigerator).
Grill or broil to desired doneness on each side.
Do not overcook.
Immediately place 2 tablespoons of cheese on top and let melt.
Serve with a hearty red wine, salad and crusty bread.

title: elephant soup
directions: Place
mice
in cage with elephant; wait 10 minutes for elephant
to
have	heart
failure.
If
elephant has not been subdued
by
his fierce opponents by this time, get more mice. When
the elephant has been sufficiently pronounced dead, wash and prepare for service.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Place in well-greased pan.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix cookies and melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Chill.
When chilled, add softened ice cream and freeze.

title: easy turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks in greased oblong baking dish.
Place turkey on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, and curry powder; pour over turkey.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle all over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato crunch(wonderful old southern recipe)
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.

title: heath candy cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil; butter foil lightly.
Break soda crackers into squares and place close together on foil.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine in pan with 1 cup brown sugar.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add soda.
Stir.
Pour over crackers and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
When done and while still hot, pour 12 ounce package (I use less) of chocolate chips over crackers and let sit a couple of minutes.
Spread melted bits over crackers.
Let cool.
Break or cut into pieces.
Tastes like Heath bars.
This covers about 40 small squares of crackers and I cut each in half (80 cookies).

title: blueberry salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water, dissolve jello.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let set.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over jello.
Sprinkle with nuts or almonds.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Next add eggs one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool right side up for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.
Mix 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour over cake while still warm to make glaze.

title: party meatballs
directions: Simmer in slow cooker until hot!

title: oven sauteed mushrooms
directions: Cut in half or slice mushrooms.
Place in baking dish. Combine parsley, garlic, salt and small amount of oil.
Pour over mushrooms and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, cheese and some oil over top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Microwave at High (100%) until apples are tender-crisp, 2 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Set apples aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Microwave at High (100%) until hot and bubbly, 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Spread over apples and microwave at Medium until done.

title: excellent pound cake
directions: Mix the cake mix with sugar, sour cream, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat all together until mixed very well. Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over crushed pineapple and juice.
Blend in whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into greased mold. Chill 2 hours.

title: trash
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in baking pan and bake at 275° for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: delectable chicken puffs
directions: Bring water
and
margarine
to
a boil.
Add flour and salt. Stir
vigorously
over
low
heat until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until smooth after
each
addition.
Stir
in 1/4 pound of processed cheese spread, mixing until melted.
Drop level tablespoonfuls of dough onto
greased
cookie
sheet.
Bake
at
400° for 25 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: oyster stuffing for the microwave
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Chop oysters.
In a 3-quart microwavable casserole, cook celery, onion and margarine, covered, on High power for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in bread crumbs, oysters, 1/4 cup oyster liquid and pepper.
Cook, covered, 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add eggs, flour, oil, cinnamon, vanilla, soda, raisins, nuts and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all beans together.
Set aside.
Simmer 15 minutes over low heat vinegar and brown sugar, stirring occasionally.
Brown bacon.
Remove bacon from grease.
Set aside.
Add to grease (use your own judgment) onions, garlic powder and mustard.
Brown lightly.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken chunks in baking dish.
Combine sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter together and put on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.
Optional:
May leave off cracker crumbs and serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken salsa
directions: Place how many boneless breasts you need in baking dish.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon or so salsa on top.
Bake for 25 minutes, then top with slice of Provolone cheese folded in half.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.
Quick and easy!

title: creamy fruit delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir. Chill slightly.
Add milk. Allow to set some, then add fruit.
Contains 51 calories per serving.

title: taco pie
directions: Make taco meat.
Butter each tortilla and layer meat, cheese and tortilla until you reach the top of your glass baking bowl. Sprinkle some water over this and microwave until cheese melts.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add ice.
May pour over crushed ice.

title: stir-fried chicken fajitas
directions: In heavy plastic bag, combine chicken strips and dressing; refrigerate for several hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Drain.

title: angel cornsticks
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring until batter is smooth.
Spoon the batter into well-greased cast-iron cornstick pans or bread pan, filling half full.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 3 dozen cornsticks.

title: stir-fry
directions: Boil meat until well done.
In a nonstick skillet, melt butter; saute peppers and onion for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce (more or less to taste) and butter.
Add meat.
Serve with white rice.
This recipe will serve 2 people.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Mix remaining flour with cranberries and nuts.
Fold into batter.
Batter will be thick.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Place in 1 gallon container and add enough water to fill container.
(This can be ice cubes.)
Chill.
Makes 30 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk, beating until smooth.
Heat 1-inch of oil to 375° in a deep skillet.
Cover bottom opening of funnel with finger.
Pour 1/4 cup batter in funnel.
Hold funnel over the center of pan and release batter into hot oil.
Move funnel in a slow circular motion to form a spiral, beginning at the center and moving outward.
Fry 2 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon or sugared fruit.

title: creamy salmon soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
In pot, saute onion in oleo; add flour and blend well.
Add juice from can of salmon; add half and half and milk.
Stir and cook until creamy.
Add bouillon, salmon and broccoli; cook about 15 minutes.
Makes a large pot of soup.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl until blended.
Place remaining ingredients and 1 cup of sauce mix in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in a 2-quart dish.
Press to form a loaf.
Pour 1/4 cup of sauce on top and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste with 1/4 cup sauce after 30 minutes of baking.
Continue baking.
When done, remove excess grease.
Pour on remaining sauce.

title: "mantecaditos"(puerto rican cookies)
directions: Blend butter and sugar, then mix flour into the blend.
Form little "balls" with the mixture and press with one finger on top to form a round dent.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
After cookies are baked, let them stand for 20 minutes.
You can sprinkle them with color crystals or nonpareils.

title: quick peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Sprinkle over peaches. Bake until light brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 12 servings.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in strips; soak in salt water for 30 minutes or longer.
Drain.
Dip in egg, then in corn meal.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix everything but hot dogs, beans and potatoes.
Cook them separately, then mix everything together.
Top with bread crumbs and onion; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix once daily for 3 days (refrigerate). On the fourth day roll tightly into 3 rolls.
Bake on broiler pan in 140° oven for 10 to 12 hours.
Do not substitute.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs with softened cream cheese and beat until well blended.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Pour powdered sugar mixture over crust and bake for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut like brownies.

title: cream of chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut in small pieces, mix with sour cream and soups.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Put 1/2 the crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with chicken mixture, then place rest of crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: christmas tree salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Blend softened cream cheese, lemon juice, orange rind, orange juice, sugar, salt and whipping cream. Fold fruit cocktail into cheese mixture and turn into refrigerator tray and freeze.
Cut into pie shaped pieces using 1-inch strip at the end for 6 trunks and 5 triangles for trees.
Serve on salad greens.

title: steak au poivre(an excellent dish for those who enjoy beef with a spicy taste.)
directions: Place the peppercorns in mortar and pestle and crush them thoroughly.
Dry the steaks on a paper towel.
Rub and press the crushed peppercorns into both sides of the meat with your fingers and the palm of your hand.
Cover with waxed paper.
Let it stand for at least half an hour, 2 or 3 hours are even better, so the flavor of the pepper will penetrate the meat.

title: chicken broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken to desired thickness.
Marinate meat in the first 6 ingredients.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Cut broccoli in 1-inch pieces.
Remove strings from pea pods.
Slant/slice into halves. Thinly slant/slice carrots.
Finely mince ginger root and garlic. Thinly slant onion.
Prepare 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water.
Heat wok. When heated, add 3 tablespoons peanut oil.
Add ginger root, garlic and onion.
Coat sides of wok to season.
Add chicken. Stir-fry chicken until lightly white.
Remove from wok.
Add 2 tablespoons peanut oil.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Stir-fry to desired texture.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, oyster sauce and pea pods.
Finish until desired texture.
Push vegetables up around side of wok.
Very slowly add cornstarch, constantly stirring until thick.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate. Spread cranberries over bottom of plate; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, then nuts. Beat eggs well; add 1 cup sugar. Beat thoroughly. Add flour, margarine and shortening. Beat well. Pour batter over cranberries. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend 2 teaspoons vanilla into can of applesauce; add baking soda.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift and stir into creamed mixture the flour and spices.
Add can of applesauce.
It will be stiff; stir well. Yields 30 muffins.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight in 4 to 6 cups water, changing water once or twice. In a large pot or Dutch oven, place ham bone, sausage, onion, celery and 3 to 4 cups water. Simmer for a couple of hours. Remove from stove and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine soft butter and sugar; mix until creamy.
Add beaten eggs; mix well, then add mashed banana.
Sift dry ingredients, add a little at a time and mix into the creamed mixture.
Add nuts, mix until smooth.
Put into greased and floured bread pan or into 1 pound coffee can.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven 65 to 70 minutes. Cool, slice thin.
This can be made ahead of time, wrapped in foil and put in freezer.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts in a brown paper bag.
Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute until syrup boils. Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn in bag.
Close and shake well.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag well and microwave another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour out on greased cookie sheet to cool.
Separate.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: aunt mae's relish
directions: Mix together and cook 3 to 4 hours or until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine and cream sugars, oleo and salad oil.
Add eggs and beat
in.
Sift
flour, soda and cream of tartar together. Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla;
mix well.
Roll dough into balls about the
size
of a walnut.
Roll in granulated sugar and place
(not too close together) on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork
dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about
dozen.
(I've
had 100.) Freezes well.

title: nut squares
directions: Melt together and spread over baked pastry while still warm. Sprinkle 1 large can of mixed nuts on top.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk or cream and horseradish together. Serve with raw cauliflower.
Very good dip.

title: strawberry candy appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill real good.
(Can chill overnight.)
Shape in the form of a strawberry.
Roll in red sugar.
Dip top in green sugar.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: waffles
directions: Separate eggs, beat egg yolks well.
Add remaining ingredients to egg yolks.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Cook on waffle iron.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Preheat broiler.
Mix hamburger, onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Form into 6 patties.
Combine tomatoes, sauce, mushrooms and oregano in a saucepan and heat.
Broil hamburgers until done to your liking.
Place hamburgers on bottom half of bun.
Top with warm sauce, cheese and an additional tablespoon of sauce.
Return to broiler until cheese melts.
Serve on faced or topped with other half of bun.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine the artichoke hearts, parmesan cheese and mayonnaise, and pour into a 9 inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20-15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato and green onions and serve with crackers.

title: spice cake
directions: Bring raisins, water and salad oil just to a boil, in a pan large enough to hold the whole recipe, stirred into raisin mixture when cooled.
Combine beaten egg and sugar and stir into raisin mixture when it has cooled.
Mix remaining ingredients well and stir into raisin mixture.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool completely in the pan on a rack.
Frost with buttercream frosting (soft butter, confectioners sugar, a bit of cream well beaten together in any amount you care for).
Leave in pan until ready to serve.
Cut into 24 squares, or cut as you need.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour with cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Cut in oleo to a fine crumbs.
Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla and add to flour and shortening mixture.
Place walnut size balls of dough (dipped in sugar) on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass or cookie stamp.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are light brown.
Cool.
Ice with Betty Crocker cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with pretty sprinkles.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine Eagle brand milk and water; add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, banana and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: eggplant patties
directions: In covered saucepan cook eggplant in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes; drain well and mash.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, egg, parsley, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties about 3-inches in diameter.
Cook in hot oil about 3 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kid's favorite chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter-flavored Crisco.

title: sauteed squid steaks
directions: Season flour with basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge steaks in flour; dip in egg.
Place on rack and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Melt butter and oil in pan.
Saute steaks quickly, two minutes per side on medium-high heat.
Remove; sprinkle with parsley and serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 6 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone it.
Grease a large casserole dish and put 1/2 package of corn bread stuffing in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt over stuffing.
Place chicken on top and pour margarine and chicken broth over the mixture.
Pour other half dry dressing over this.
Beat eggs in milk and pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 2 hours before cooking.
Put soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Bake, covered.

title: baked potato cheese casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice margarine on top.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until soft. Sprinkle real bacon bits on top and serve.

title: quiche
directions: Spread meat in unbaked pie shell.
Spread cheese over meat. Mix sour cream, eggs and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Bake 5 minutes at 400° and finish at 350° until brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cake mix and butter.
You can add 1 c. chopped nuts to the pumpkin if desired.
Pour into 9 by 13 in. cake pan, sprinkle cake mix over batter and drizzle butter over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
Very rich.

title: country pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pat mixture into bottom and sides of well-greased 9-inch pie plate.

title: candied sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Boil potatoes until slightly tender, but not well done.
Peel and slice apples.
Arrange layers of potatoes and apples in well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix butter, sugar, water and salt well and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Blend all together for 3 minutes on medium speed; pour into buttered bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Spread butter on top.
Cut and serve warm or cold.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat ground meat uncooked in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Place sliced onion over meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Add grated cheese.
Mix celery soup and evaporated milk and heat a little. Pour over other ingredients.
Top with tater tots and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: steve's applesauce cake
directions: Combine applesauce, butter, sugar and egg.
Add sifted mixture of flour, salt, cinnamon, allspice, ginger, cloves and nutmeg. Add raisins and nuts.
Mix and bake in tube or loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new year's day dinner
directions: Adjust quantities of ingredients to serve the number of guests expected.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Start with about 2 cups of flour that has baking powder and baking soda added to it. Stir out most of the lumps, then add eggs, sour cream and buttermilk. Thin down with sweet milk if necessary. Cook on hot griddle.

title: waffles
directions: Put buttermilk in mixing bowl.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix flour, salt, soda and sugar together.
Then add to buttermilk, eggs and butter slowly.
Beat, then add egg whites which have been well beaten.
Stir in egg whites (don't beat).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry orange jam
directions: Use containers (one pint or less) with tight lids.
Wash and scald or use dishwasher with very hot water.

title: ma sheffler's fast pirogies
directions: 1. Cook lasagna noodles until done. Wash and drain. Cook potatoes, drain and mash adding milk and margarine to
make creamy.
2. Saute sliced onions in oleo. In 9 x 13 x 2 pan layer 1/2 the onions and melted margarine, then 4 of the
lasagna noodles, then the mashed potatoes.
3. Cover with the other 4 lasagna noodles. Spread rest of
onions and margarine on top. Cover with aluminum foil
(prick a few holes) and bake on cookie sheet at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: 4 b's tomato soup #1
directions: Mix all, but the cream, and simmer.
Heat cream separately and add to the hot mixture. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: scuzball
directions: Cut wafer ham in small, bite size pieces.
Mix with onions. Blend ham and onions with cream cheese.
Shape into large ball. Serve with crackers or chips.
Great for holidays or family gatherings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Make and chill jello.
Blend in mayonnaise, nuts and fruit. Add chicken last.
Serves 6 to 8 servings.

title: ground beef or ground turkey and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground meat, onion and pepper together.
Drain fat off.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, mushrooms and spices.
Simmer.
Prepare crust.
Separate dough and press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan (9-inch or 10-inch). Combine egg and 1 cup cheese and spread over crust.
Spoon meat mix over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Slice strawberries; add sugar.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Serve with pound cake or angel food cake.

title: green salad sandwich spread
directions: Mix gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve mixture over hot water. Add mayonnaise and then the vegetables.
Mix well and chill. Spread on white or wheat sandwich bread and cut into small party sandwiches.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Combine everything.
Heat to boiling (15 to 20 minutes) on High in microwave.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.

title: horseradish deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from eggs; lengthwise cut eggs. Set whites aside. In a bowl, mash the yolks until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, and mix well. Fill egg whites with the yolk mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate before serving. Makes 1 dozen.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise; remove yolks.
Place yolks in a bowl; mash with a fork until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and pickle juice.
Add garlic, celery, sweetener and salt and pepper to taste.
Mixture should be smooth.
If too dry, add pickle juice, vinegar and mayonnaise until texture and taste are just right. fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika or parsley.
Makes 24.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Melt buttah in a casserole dish 'n fix chicken in layers wid onions 'n mushrooms...kiver 'n cook fur 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Now take chicken out to rest a min...pore enuff boilin' watah in mushroom juice to make 4 1/2 cups uv broth...drap bouillon cubes in broth to dissolve.
Dump the rice 'n broth in casserole 'n put back in the oven fur another hour.

title: almond pretzels or mandelplattchen
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add sifted sugar gradually and blend until creamy.
Beat in egg yolks, eggs and sour cream.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and lemon rind.
Chill the dough several hours until easy to handle. Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape the dough into long, thin rolls and twist these into pretzel shape.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Brush with French egg wash.
Sprinkle the tops with chopped blanched almonds and sugar.
Bake at once for 10 to 15 minutes. Do not let the pretzels color.
Makes 2 dozen 2-inch pretzels.

title: oyster rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Open oysters.
With knife, remove oysters from shells; drain oysters.
Wash shells.
Place each oyster in deep half of shell.
Combine parsley, onion, and 1 tablespoon melted butter; spread over oysters.
Sprinkle with a little salt, pepper, and paprika.
Top each with 2 teaspoons spinach, then 1/2 teaspoon bread crumbs.
Dot each with about 1 teaspoon butter, and sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella.
Arrange shells on bed of rock salt in a shallow pan.
Bake till cheese is melted and browned, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 12-inch casserole.

title: tomato macaroni casserole
directions: In a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish, combine the macaroni, tomatoes and 3/4 cup cheese; mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes; stir.
Cover and heat 1 minute longer.
Sprinkle with bacon and remaining cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, for 30 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cream together your cream cheese and add powdered sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Spread over top of cooled crumbs.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Mix Dream Whip as directed and spread over cream cheese and nuts.
Top with a can of prepared cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: french quarter steak
directions: Marinate meat 4 hours or overnight if possible, 3/4 time in refrigerator, 1/4 out, using the ingredients as a marinating sauce.
Puncture meat with a fork to better allow sauce to penetrate meat.
Cook quickly over hot fire.
Slice very thin across the grain of meat.

title: crispy chocolate log
directions: Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil.
Grease lightly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure and sift again with salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening, 2 tablespoons of milk and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add banana pulp.
Combine remaining milk and vanilla.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; top chicken.
Stir soup and spread over chicken; combine oleo and crushed stuffing and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mashed potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can fried onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon potato mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Using back of spoon, spread potatoes across bottom and up sides of dish to form shell.

title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sour cream, vinegar, sugar, dill, salt and pepper.
Gently toss in cucumbers and onion, stirring gently to mix.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda and set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and drop onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into halves lengthwise.
Combine the flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in a bag, coating well.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in order the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add a little at a time.
Add apples and coconut, then add nuts last.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the eggs, applesauce, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened (batter will be thick). Stir in carrots, apple, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 24 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Yield: 2 dozen muffins.

title: beanie weenie
directions: Cook on medium heat until hot.
Serve.

title: toasted pecan halves
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar.
Beat together and add salt; then dip pecan halves in mixture.
Place pecan halves on slightly greased cookie sheet (each one separately). Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: the best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large saucepan until hot. Transfer to baking pan or bean pot.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Enjoy!!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo, beat in eggs. Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and allspice. Add chopped apples.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Cut bacon and onions in small pieces; combine with ground beef and brown in skillet.
Drain and mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add lemon juice and rind, salt, egg yolks, milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or try 350° for 35 minutes.
Center should be firm.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour and salt, cut in shortening and mix together until crumbly. Put in water and form into 2 balls. Roll out 1 ball for bottom crust.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Skin and remove meat from bones and chop.
Mix soup cream, soup, paprika and dill weed. Add chicken and mix.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Crush crackers and toss lightly in melted oleo.
Sprinkle on casserole top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
May be frozen. Serves 12.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil and eggs, one at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Top with sifted powdered sugar.

title: frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, mix milk and flour over medium-low heat, stirring until it makes a paste consistency.
Set aside to cool. In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar and Crisco until mixture feels smooth.
Add paste mixture to mixing bowl and beat well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla and mix again.
Frosting is ready unless you want to color it, which you can do with food coloring.
Be creative and enjoy.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Put apples and applesauce on pizza crust then bake in oven at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Can add 1 cup or less chopped pecans. Shape in a ball with waxed paper. Sprinkle with chili powder. Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in pan.
Cover pan until mixture starts to boil.
Insert thermometer in uncovered pan and cook mixture until thermometer reaches 248°.
Do not stir while mixture cooks and do not scrape sides of pan.
When mixture reaches 248°, just dump it into a bowl.
Add butter and vanilla and walk away from that bowl until the mixture feels lukewarm or cooler.
It takes just a few minutes of beating for mixture to reach temperature for pouring into a buttered pie tin or other pan to "set."
Cut and enjoy.

title: salami pie
directions: Spread rolls/dough in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cheese and salami. Add well beaten eggs.
Blend well.
Spread evenly on crust and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
(Can be frozen and reheated.)

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil water, sugar and salt until mixture forms a hard ball. Cool mixture slightly.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Beat.
Spoon on buttered plate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars together.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add pudding and mix.
Sift flour and soda together.
Mix all ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon out by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
These turn out soft and delicious.

title: cream puff cake
directions: To boiling water, add butter.
