Put in large mixing bowl and add flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, then beat 1 minute.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli still frozen in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Boil chicken for 20 minutes.
Put chicken over broccoli.
Break into pieces.
Pour 2 cups of chicken broth water in pot.

title: super crisp country fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg in a medium bowl; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a bag.
Add a few pieces of chicken to coat.
Dip chicken in milk and egg mixture.
Shake a second time in flour mixture.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together. Grease and flour a baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in a double boiler, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa; add shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Put in bottom of unbaked pie crust. Mix 3 eggs and 1/4 cup sugar, corn syrup and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over first layer. Top with 1 1/4 cups whole pecans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken italiano(low-fat)
directions: Combine chicken and 1/2 dressing; saute.
Add veggies and rest of dressing.
Cover.
Simmer for 7 to 9 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: philly steak sandwiches
directions: Toast an English muffin for each person. Spread toasted English muffin halves with seafood or crab salad. Place 1 slice of a large tomato on salad. Sprinkle with shredded cheese (Colby, Monterey Jack, Mozzarella or your favorite). Place in toaster oven or on your broiler pan and broil until the cheese melts, but is not browned. Serve.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well; set aside.
Cook noodles as directed; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of sauce to spinach; spoon this into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with Colby cheese. Add 1/2 cup of sauce to noodles; spoon over cheese.
Spoon remaining sauce over noodle layer; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well
and
pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook 3/4 cup sugar with the reserved pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Mix cherries, pineapple, oranges and syrup. After syrup is cold, add the bananas cut into small pieces. Chill and serve in large salad bowl.
Garnish with fresh mint. Serves 6.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble bread in a large bowl.
Chop onions (including green parts), radishes, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add to bread crumbs.

title: veal in caper sauce
directions: Pound veal slices to a uniform 1/4-inch thickness with a meat mallet.
Heat oil and half the butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Coat veal in flour and brown both sides in the hot skillet. Transfer to a warm platter and season with salt and pepper.
Remove skillet from heat; add lemon juice, capers, parsley and remaining butter.
Stir.
Briefly warm sauce to medium heat.
Pour sauce over veal on warm platter.
Garnish with lemon slices and serve.
Serves 4.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt in food processor. Gradually add water and vinegar mixture.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Make into pie crusts or cobbler.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: hot spiced apple juice
directions: Stud lemon slices with cloves.	Place one slice in each cup. Heat
apple juice to just below boiling.
Pour hot juice into cups and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions; drain.
Mix soup, mayo, egg, onion, salt and pepper and broccoli in a big bowl.
Melt butter and put in stuffing mix; grease bottom of casserole; place herb stuffing in bottom.
Pour in broccoli mixture; sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 350° until it bubbles.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Cook on medium heat until it starts to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator and serve when set.

title: crab ragoons
directions: Place dried onion in small bowl and add just enough water to cover, and let set for 10 minutes.
Add to cream cheese, sugar, and crabmeat.
Spread egg around edges of wonton wrapper, then place 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in center, then seal edges by pinching together.
Deep fry for a few seconds and drain on paper towels.

title: southern sausage biscuits
directions: Mix well. Roll into tiny balls (about the size of a nickel). Cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain on a wire rack covered with a paper towel. They may be frozen.
To reheat, bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Blend well the butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, peanut butter, soda and salt.
Add vanilla, flour and oatmeal.
Pat onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: texanna beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water and baking soda.
Drain.
Cover with fresh water and cook until tender.
Saute onion and garlic in a little oil.
Brown the meat.
Mix all other ingredients into this mixture.
Add to cooked beans and cook all together until the flavors are well blended.

title: brie cheese spread
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Do not separate but press all crescent rolls together, forming square sheet or pastry.
Wrap cheese in pastry and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is of spreading consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: old-fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans (8 x 9-inch).
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: old timey nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in usual manner, adding flour coated nuts last.
Bake 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan at 350°.

title: philadelphia fish chowder, 1886
directions: Cut fish, potatoes, onion and bacon or ham into pieces about 1/2-inch square.
Put bacon and onion into a frying pan; stir and fry them a light brown.

Put a layer of potatoes in saucepan; then a layer of fish; then a sprinkling of onion and bacon; then a layer of tomatoes; then sprinkle of thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper and continue alternating until all is in (last layer is potatoes).
Add water.
Cover with lid and simmer over moderate fire for 20 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine well, mix until well blended.
Chill 1/2 hour make into balls and roll in crushed pecans - can add parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Form teaspoonfuls of dough into balls and drop into sugar to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until cookie has partially flattened and browned.
Cookies will flatten and crinkle.
Makes 5 1/2 to 7 dozen cookies depending on size of cookies you've made.
If you make very small cookies, watch them closely for baking time.

title: grapefruit cape
directions: Crush 6 to 8 leaves of mint with the sugar and sprinkle it over the grapefruit segments.
Macerate in the refrigerator for several hours.
Serve in a chilled sherbet glass or goblet with a mint sprig on top.

title: sicilian baked macaroni
directions: Slice large eggplant lengthwise and brown in oil.
In a separate pan, saute mushrooms lightly. When eggplant is done, let dry on paper towels.

title: nacho potato salad
directions: Place potatoes into a large cooking pot and cover with cold water.
Boil on medium-high until a fork slips easily into them (approximately 40 to 45 minutes).
Allow potatoes to cool before peeling them.
While potatoes are cooling, chop and boil broccoli for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dice onion and tomato and set aside.
Dice peeled potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes and place into a large bowl. Drain broccoli and place into the bowl with the potatoes.
Mix broccoli and potatoes together.
Top with peppers, bacon bits and tomato.
Top with cheese and mix ingredients again.
Add the tortilla chips last, just before serving, and mix (if crisp chips are desired, because chips will soften after in mixture for a couple of hours).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and stir until thawed.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave at 50% power for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: green layered salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place a layer shredded lettuce, layer of onion, layer of chopped celery and layer of cooled peas. Continue to layer but end up with lettuce on top.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Mix eggs, butter, honey and sugar until smooth.
Sprinkle coconut over pie shell.
Top with egg mixture.
Sprinkle Macadamia nuts over filling.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine and sugars.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Form in balls. Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
With bottom of glass or jar (also coated with sugar), press each cookie flat.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
You can use different flavoring and nuts if desired.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add the rest and stir to moisten.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: apple gingerbread upside-down cake
directions: Melt fat in boiling water.
Add molasses.
Sift flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Arrange apples, cinnamon and sugar in buttered baking dish or heavy pan.
Pour the gingerbread mixture over the apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn the gingerbread out carefully, upside-down.
Serve hot or cold with hard sauce or cream.

title: mini hamburgers(yield: 24 hamburgers)
directions: 1. Mix 1st five ingredients.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls over a pizza pan and bake at 350° about 10 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix together all vegetables and the 3/4 cup cheese.
Then put this on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with other grated cheese, olives and Mozzarella.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; then cook until melted the marshmallows with the sugar and milk.
Pour over the cake while hot; when it cools, ice with chocolate icing.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat butter, sugar, syrup and salt together.
Stir to dissolve sugar; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir well.
Pour over popcorn, bake 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue kraut
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in the pan.
Then drain off fat.
Drain sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Pour over cream cheese mix. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool, then chill.

title: frankfurter fanfare
directions: Combine mustard and jelly in chafing dish or double boiler. Slice frankfurters diagonally into bite size pieces.
Add to sauce.
Heat thoroughly.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Artichoke hearts, cherry tomatoes, black olives and mushrooms should be sliced thin.
Mix ingredients together and use marinade from artichoke to dress.
Top with black pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Yummy!
Enjoy!

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken with onion in margarine.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, milk and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover. Simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken. Melt cheese and pour sauce over chicken.

title: nutty pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, 3/4 cup melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar and place in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool before adding the next layers.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip and layer on pretzel mix.

title: country cookies
directions: Note:
I always add lots of pecans (chopped).

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fry until golden brown.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt a stick of butter in bowl which you are going to use.
Mix the sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt together; mix well. Pour in a buttered pan, then put 1 can of fruit (kind desired) or fresh berries on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: On half power, microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butterscotch chips for 4 minutes.
Mix together.
Add marshmallows and peanuts; put in 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate.
To serve, cut in squares.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add Velveeta cheese and heat until cheese is melted. Spoon mixture onto rye bread.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Serve and enjoy!

title: ham quiche wedges
directions: Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Press dough on bottom and up sides of greased 12-inch pizza pan with floured hands.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Mix eggs, sour cream, cheese, onions and onion salt; pour over crust.
Sprinkle ham over egg mixture.
Bake until set, about 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Add Bisquick baking mix all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, approximately 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat until smooth.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls (12 to be exact), 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet away from drafts.
Cut off tops and remove any soft dough.
Fill and enjoy!

title: delicious grape dessert
directions: Alternate layers of grapes, sour cream and a sprinkling of brown sugar in a compote.

title: gluh wein
directions: Remove centers from the fruit slices.
In a large saucepan (stainless steel or heat resistant glass), bring wine to simmering; do not boil.
Add fruit and rest of ingredients; stir to dissolve sugar.
Over low heat, let stand about 10 minutes. Serve in punch cups, mugs or coffee cups.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurts with Cool Whip.
Spread mixture into crust and cover.
Freeze 1 to 2 hours.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Yogurt can be any kind, strawberry, banana, cherry, etc.

title: english muffins
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water.
Make a well in 5 cups of flour.
Pour in milk and water.
Mix with a fork.
Dough will be sticky.
Add 1 more cup of flour, a little at a time, kneading after each addition.
May only use 1/2 cup of flour.

title: cheese beer soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, carrots, celery, water, butter and bouillon.
Bring to boil, covered.
Reduce heat and simmer until veggies are tender.

title: tuna au gratin
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in baking dish and top with an additional 1 1/2 tablespoons catsup. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 2.

title: peach bavarian dessert
directions: Drain peaches.
Reserve 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces.
Set aside.
In bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar with boiling water.
Stir in 2/3 cup of juice.
Chill until slightly thickened; stir in almond extract in Cool Whip.
Fold gently into gelatin.
Reserve some Cool Whip for top of dessert.
Fold in peaches.
Chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and additional peaches, if desired.

title: kraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onions together; drain off fat.
Mix in all other ingredients, chill until firm.
Make into small balls, chill again.
Beat together 2 eggs and 1/2 cup milk.
Roll balls into flour, then dip into the egg mixture, then roll into the bread crumbs and deep fry.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to large bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: spiced peach dessert(for diabetics)
directions: Drain peaches; reserve juice. Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in saucepan. Stir in peach juice and blend well. Add peaches and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add orange extract and brown sugar substitute.
Mix well and serve hot.

title: jello layer dessert
directions: Fix Jell-O per directions on package, less 1/2 cup water.
Mix blueberry pie filling and pineapple with juice into Jell-O mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and chill.
Next, mix cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar together until smooth.
Pour over chilled Jell-O mixture.
Yummy!

title: christmas salad
directions: Set jello according to package instructions.
Cut into cubes and fold 3/4 of jello, drained fruit and nuts into 3/4 of whipped cream.
Place in serving bowl.
Top with the remaining jello cubes and frost with the remaining cream.

title: two pecan pies
directions: Pour sugar, add eggs; melt butter.
Add all together.
Mix in pecans last.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch iron skillet.
Thaw broccoli and mix with all ingredients, adding 1/2 melted butter to batter.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chiketti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat the ingredients for 4 minutes.
Makes three layers.
Bake at 350°. Cool.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/4 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: good ole hush puppies
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add flour, corn meal and milk; mix well.
Add onion, cheese and Texas Pete; stir in well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Serve.

title: favorite cream pie(banana or otherwise)
directions: Scald milk and cream in top of double boiler.
Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt and mix together thoroughly.
Add to scalded milk and cook until thick and smooth.
Then cook 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of mixture to beaten egg yolks; return to double boiler and cook a few minutes longer.
Cool and add vanilla and/or sliced bananas. (You can use the whites of the two eggs in your meringue.)

title: hungry man casserole(or anyone else!)
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 13 x 9 pan or large casserole.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine 2 cups bran and boiling water; set aside.
Cream together until fluffy the shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add the buttermilk.
Stir in the All-Bran and add hot bran mixture.
Blend. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This mixture keeps in refrigerator for 6 to 8 weeks.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, puncture top with fork.
Pour pineapple and juice over cake.
Let cool.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Pour over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 by 9 inch cake pan.
Beat cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream in large bowl on medium speed for 2 minutes, scrapping bowl occasionally.
Spread half of the batter in the pan.
Stir together brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon; spread over the batter.
Carefully spread remaining batter over cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place pan in preheated oven for about 45 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Prick surface of the warm cake several times with a fork.
Spread glaze over the cake.
Cool completely.
This is also good served warm with butter.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Stir together sour cream, Cheddar cheese and soup.
Stir in hash browns.
Top with corn flakes.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: orange shake
directions: Blend on high 30 seconds.

title: tomato basil tart
directions: Bake pie crust 9 minutes at 450°.
Reset oven to 375°.
Cool shell and add 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese to crust.
Layer tomatoes on cheese.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Sprinkle chopped basil on tomatoes.
Mix remaining Mozzarella, mayonnaise, Parmesan and pepper; spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden.

title: spicy wings
directions: Toss wings with the other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Then add 1 cup flour to wings. Toss to coat.
Spray baking sheets with Pam spray.
Place wings on sheets and spray with spray.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and crispy.
Serve with Bleu cheese or Ranch dressing and celery.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add only 3 cups of the flour slowly; add vanilla.
Put remaining cup of flour on nuts; toss, then add to cake batter.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: double delicious dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, press the melted margarine or butter with the graham cracker crumbs to the bottom of the pan.
Shake on the chips, nuts and coconut over the entire concoction.
Pour the sweetened, condensed milk over the concoction.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool and cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature if you can keep them that long.

title: lazy pie crust cobbler
directions: Put a stick of oleo in a pan and let melt.
Meanwhile, mix well the flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over melted oleo and add sweetened canned fruit.
Cook about 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Presto, crust and fruit on bottom and top too.

title: never fail cupcakes
directions: Put all ingredients together in order given; beat thoroughly. Fill cupcake pans 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: linaga (boiled chicken stew)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chicken pieces, water, ginger, peppercorns, salt, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil; lower heat, cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Add cabbage and green onions and cook until soft. Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg. Add chocolate, milk and baking soda. Add flour. Mix well. Add chopped cherries and juice. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook rice according to directions.

title: lemon-strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in oleo and egg yolks.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool. Arrange strawberries on top of filling.
Combine Cool Whip, powdered sugar and coconut. Spread over strawberries.
Add coconut on top and additional strawberries.
Chill at least 6 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello, water, strawberries and mashed bananas.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture in dish.
Let congeal. Spread sour cream over congealed mix.
Add other 1/2 and let congeal.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with 1 cup of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon together in separate bowl.
Cut in butter very well.
Start with pastry blender, end with fingers. Sprinkle evenly over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Recipe easily halved.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Serves 6.

title: almond joy brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add butter, eggs and almond extract and stir.
Use your hands to thoroughly blend mixture.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 12 inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut brownies into 2 inch squares.
Enjoy!

title: tuna balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for ten minutes in a 300° oven.

title: stromboli
directions: On lightly greased cookie sheet, spread pizza dough to corners.
Layer with topping to within 1 inch of edges and roll from long side.
Seal all edges and cut 1-inch slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let cool slightly and cut into slices.

title: creole eggplant
directions: Saute onion in olive oil and butter.
Add garlic, green pepper, tomatoes, eggplant, salt, and peppers.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
If desired, at serving time, add breadcrumbs to thicken.
Yields 4 servings.
Serve over rice.
It is an excellent side for seafood.

title: do ahead bran muffins
directions: Dump everything into a large bowl.
Mix well.
Cover in airtight container and store in refrigerator.
This mixture will store for up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator or 3 to 6 months in the freezer.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Cut steak in 2-inch squares.
Heat oil in skillet.
Coat steak in flour and salt.
Brown in oil.
Move steak over to side and add remaining ingredients.
Then place steak on top of this.
Pour one cup of water over and cook at 250° until vegetables are tender, about 35 minutes.

title: mrs. james rhodes' corn chowder(ohio governor's wife)
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Add cream-style corn, milk, whipping cream and salt.
Cook until finished.

title: barbecue beef patties
directions: Mix all ingredients real well and pat out into burgers and fry until done.

title: tropical cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake according to directions. Before using mixer to thicken, add the 1/2 cup coconut, crushed pineapple and nuts. Pour in prepared 9 x 12 pan. Toast 3/4 cup coconut in oven until golden brown and sprinkle on cheesecake. Refrigerate until set. Slice and enjoy!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients except Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 into refrigerator to set.
Leave 1/2 at room temperature.
When refrigerated 1/2 is set, spread with Cool Whip.
Top with room temperature 1/2 mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco with a fork until lumpy.
Add water and mix into a soft dough.
Roll out bottom crust.
Fill with apples.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and flour in bowl.
Sprinkle over apples.
Slice 2 tablespoons of oleo over top and add top crust.
Brush with can milk.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: mustard string beans
directions: Put together in a pan with the juice from the string beans. Stir until smooth.
Add string beans and heat.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cut butter in flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
After cutting in, add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla flavoring.
Chill if you like.
Roll out on floured board and use a number 3 cutter, such as a glass, measuring 3-inches across.
Bake until brown on top in a 450° oven, about 8 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: fruit bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in cottage cheese and fruit; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Fry onion, bell pepper, celery and onion tops in 2 large cooking size spoons of corn oil until light brown.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Cook until thick.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender; drain well.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: maw maw's potato salad(student favorite)
directions: Boil potatoes until they are tender.
Boil eggs until done. Peel and cube potatoes.
Sprinkle potatoes with celery salt, white pepper and salt to taste.
Coat the potatoes with mustard.
Stir in sweet relish to taste.
Add in fat-free Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to taste.
Chop and add eggs.
Serve warm or cold.
This keeps well for several days.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt, pepper, nuts and cheese.
Cream butter and mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Mold into 2 rolls and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thinly and bake at 359° until lightly browned (10 to 12 minutes).
May be made ahead and frozen in rolls until ready for use.
Great for parties.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk, heating thoroughly. Add cheese, heating and stirring until cheese melts.
Combine with noodle mixture.
Spoon into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add all other ingredients and cook in saucepan for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve over Fritos chips or Tostitos.

title: swiss cheese fondue(microwave)
directions: Combine flour, seasonings and milk in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Beat with rotary beater or wire whisk until smooth. Stir in cheese.
Add butter.
Cover with a glass lid.

title: duffie's deer camp stew
directions: This recipe will feed 15 people.
Use 2 pounds of stew meat. Brown in frying pan and put in 3 gallon cooker.
Add water and bring to boil; boil until tender.
Cut up and add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Add tomatoes.
Add salt, black pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Cover with water and bring to boil. Cut heat to simmer and cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve with crackers or bread and deer camp coffee or other drinks.
I guarantee hunters will like this recipe.

title: mexican bloody mary
directions: Fill a highball glass with ice.
Add tequila, tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and celery salt.
Stir.
Garnish with lime wedge and chili pepper.
Can be served without alcohol.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8 inch thick.
Press circles to cover bottom and sides of 9x13-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with bread slices. Put cheese and bacon on the bread. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread. Bake in a pan of water at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 12 to 15.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ritz meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients except for 5 Ritz crackers and bacon strips.
Mold into loaf.
Crumble remaining crackers on loaf.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: date krispie balls
directions: Melt butter, dates and sugar together.
Mix Rice Krispies and vanilla in last.
Roll in coconut.
These are easy and the texture and flavor are great.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and sugar together until tender; drain and gently mash. Dot small casserole with 1/2 the margarine. Alternate layers (2 layers) of the squash mixture, half and half and cheese slices (broken into pieces) and black pepper. Dot with remaining half of margarine. Top with crumbs. Bake, covered, 350° until bubbly and slightly browned, about 20 minutes.

title: little pizza appetizers
directions: Place buns on cookie sheet.
Spread with sauce and top with favorite toppings and cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and buns brown at edges.
Serve immediately.

title: mama's old fashion coconut pound cake
directions: Defrost coconut.
Eggs and butter should be room temperature, probably overnight.
Spray tube pan with Pam.
Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend.
Stir in coconut.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: holiday appetizer dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper; mix well.
Stir in sour cream and walnuts.
Place in small shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with assorted crackers.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar, margarine, eggs, orange powder and vanilla until thick (10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and cereals.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in coconut.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Parboil zucchini 5 minutes.
Drain.
Dip in cold water.
Saute ground beef and onion and drain.
Salt to taste.
Add oregano and garlic if desired.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put layer of zucchini on bottom, meat and rice next, then cottage cheese (dab here and there).
Spread mushroom soup on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix soups and water. Pour 3/4 of this mixture over rice.
Stir well. Top rice with chicken.
Cut butter into chunks and place on chicken.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken. Cover all with cheese and paprika.
Cover and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until rice is tender.

title: smothered steaks
directions: Combine the flour and salt in a slightly deep plate.
Cover steaks with the flour mixture.
In a deep dish or crock-pot, pour in the water.
Place steaks in the pot and sprinkle the chopped onions over the top.
Let cook for 30 to 45 minutes or until desired.
Great with vegetables and rice.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine the vegetables and enough Hidden Valley Ranch dressing just to moisten the vegetables.

title: salmon seashell salad
directions: Drain salmon; break into chunks.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool.
Combine salmon, macaroni, corn, green pepper, radishes, olives and mustard in a bowl.
Fold in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 7 minutes, then add next 3 ingredients.
Add nuts, if desired. Put in a buttered dish, let cool and cut.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Crunch potato chips and add pepper and garlic salt.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and roll in crumbs.
Place pieces in pan, skin side up, making sure they are not touching. Pour remaining butter and crumbs over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not turn chicken.

title: spicy cranberry-orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Fold in cranberries, orange and nuts.
Makes 10 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute garlic and onion in 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Add sliced zucchini, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; stir to mix.
Spoon into a lightly greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts and bread crumbs are lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Place in casserole dish, mixing both soups with broccoli. Layer cheese on top.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Place cucumbers whole or in strips and pack in quart jar.
Add dill seed and garlic.
Heat other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Arrange vegetables in bowl with tight-fitting lid.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate. Keeps 3 to 4 weeks.

title: arizona rice
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients except eggs.
Fold in eggs.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 80 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Place soup into a skillet; pour in boiling water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, shrimp, celery, green pepper, curry, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook at 205° until rice and shrimp are done.
Add olives, sprinkle with almonds.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sugar cookies(adapted from 1796 recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop pieces as large as walnuts onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Sprinkle with flour, then sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken and rice skillet
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown chicken.
Add tomatoes, water, onion, green pepper, garlic and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and return to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed into rice.

title: potato fries(no fat - no oil)
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Cut each into eight sections.
Place on cookie sheets and place in oven at 400°.
Rotate every 20 minutes until done.
Usually takes 40 minutes.

title: picante dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Add onion and picante sauce; whip until creamy.

title: jiffy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: honey nutters
directions: Mix well peanut butter, honey, dry milk and graham crackers. Shape into small balls and roll in toasted wheat germ.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour, meal, beer and salt in a bowl, using a whisk. Let sit for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at room temperature.
Thirty minutes before batter is ready, preheat oven to 200°.
Peel and slice onions; separate into rings.
Heat oil and batter onion rings. Fry in oil until brown and place in a casserole in oven until golden brown and crispy.
Do not stack.
Can freeze!!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the hot water over the oatmeal. Mix the sugars, oil and eggs. Beat 5 minutes. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add flour mixture and oatmeal to sugar mixture and beat 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp and chicken dinner
directions: *Will serve 6 people with 2 pounds of shrimp.
If desired more shrimp can be added.
Same goes for chicken.
You can use white or dark chicken.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Stir all ingredients together, except flour.
Add first 2 cups of flour and mix well.
Stir in remaining 2 cups of flour.
Cover bowl and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: marzetti slaw salad
directions: *I use Dole slaw in package with carrots.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in water.
Heat soup until hot.
Stir in mayonnaise, dissolved gelatin and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add crab meat, celery and onion.
Pour into 4-cup mold, slightly oiled, and let set.

title: peanut butter cookies(great for kids, no bake)
directions: Measure peanut butter, marshmallow cream and chocolate chips together in large bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Form into balls and roll into graham crackers.
Very good.

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix marmalade with 1 teaspoon of vanilla; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg, milk, marmalade and remaining teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Place in large, greased loaf pan.
Let stand 10 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh asparagus with lemon(healthful eating)
directions: Wash asparagus; snap stalks.
Place on vegetable steamer rack over boiling water.
Cover and steam 5 to 6 minutes, just until barely tender.

title: nikki's easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Brown in non-stick skillet until done.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain chicken and spread evenly in 9x13-inch pan.
Pour mixed vegetables over chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix chicken soup and 1 cup of chicken broth until well blended.
Pour over mixed vegetables in pan.
In a clean bowl, combine Bisquick and milk and mix until smooth.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 30-45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6-8.

title: apple harvest cake with glaze
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend all ingredients except apples and nuts until moistened; beat 3 minutes longer at medium speed. By hand, stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 65 minutes.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Mix beef and gravy with Veg-All.
Pour into one of the pie shells.
Put together pie shell on top; seal edges together.
Make slits in top of crust.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: debbie's zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cranberry quick bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with juice, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes, remove from pan.
Serve with Sweet Orange Spread. Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruity punch for kids
directions: Combine concentrates, drink mix and sugar.
Gradually add water.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
When set, add egg, Bisquick and nuts.
Roll into small balls; mash with fork. Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Equal on top when they are cool.

title: vegetable combination
directions: Cook cauliflower and spinach separately as directed on package; drain.
Toss cauliflower with spinach.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack in each jar:
cucumbers, 2 beads of garlic, 1/2 teaspoon alum, 1 head of dill and 1 grape leaf.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo together.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Put in nuts; microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes and take out.
Mix in soda; stir until frothy.
Stir quickly onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cream margarine and flour.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Blend in milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill. Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix beans, onion and pepper in crock-pot.
Brown ground beef and put on top of beans.
Put barbecue sauce over meat; don't mix. Cook in crock-pot on low heat for 2 hours.
Turn on high and cook for 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts in madeira sauce
directions: Pound each breast and generously spread each side with lemon juice.
Sprinkle white pepper on each side of the breasts.
In large skillet saute breasts over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Turn heat to high for about 1 minute to deglaze pan.
Add bouillon and wine and cook down to syrup consistency.
Turn heat to medium to medium-high and add cream.
Allow mixture to bubble up and settle down.
Serve breasts over rice with sauteed mushrooms and tossed salad.

title: italian lunch loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour; serve hot or chill and slice for sandwiches.
Cooking time: 1 hour.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Cover 2 cups seedless raisins with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drain.
To flour and salt add shortening.
Blend thoroughly.
Add soda and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Make a well in center and add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Add drained raisins.
Stir and mix thoroughly, then place on floured board.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness and bake on a moderately hot griddle.
When lower side is nicely browned, turn with pancake turner.

title: chocolate beer
directions: *Substitute ginger ale (1 to 2 bottles).

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate with coffee in top of double boiler.
Stir until smooth; cool.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add cooled chocolate; blend well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition, beating for a total of 15 minutes.
In another large bowl with clean beaters, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into chocolate mixture. Measure and refrigerate 1/4 of the mixture.
Pour remainder of chocolate mixture into greased (bottom only) 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool completely in pan on cake rack.
(Cake will sink in the middle.) Spread reserved chocolate mixture over top.
Cover and chill overnight.
Garnish with confectioners sugar.
Serve in thin slices.
Serves 12 people.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Prepare chicken stock, skim off fat if necessary.
Add to stock salt to taste, pepper and food coloring (optional).

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: date roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk, dates and cherries in pot. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook to soft ball stage or 236° on candy thermometer.
Take off fire; add oleo.
Allow to cool until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until it thickens. Pour onto damp towels and mold into roll about 2-inches thick. Roll completely in towel and allow to cool.
When cold, remove towel and slice.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers, cut in short, narrow strips.
Weigh cucumbers.
You need 7 pounds after they are peeled and cut up. Soak in pickling lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse three times.
Cover with ice for 3 hours, drain.
Bring to boil 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and red cinnamon drops.
Pour over drained cucumbers.
Let stand another 24 hours.
Pour off syrup and bring to a boil.
Pack pickles into pint jars.
Pour boiling syrup over pickles in jar and seal.
Yields 12 to 14 pints.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine beef and next 6 ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Form into small balls (90).
Place into skillet. Brown.
Combine chili sauce, cranberry sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice in a large pan.
Simmer.
Pour in meat balls and simmer for 1 hour in sauce.

title: indian bread
directions: Add enough milk to other ingredients to make a stiff dough. Add milk, mixing with hands until stiff dough is formed.
Add flour if sticky.
Roll out and use your favorite cookie cutters or cut in squares.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, until golden, then turn. Remove when they float to top.
Eat plain or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry the bacon, peppers and onion, then pour off the grease and add the rice, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: family hamburger casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion
and	celery	until
meat
loses it's color. Drain extra fat.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, salt, pepper and half of cheese.	Pour
into
a greased casserole.
Combine crumbs and remaining cheese
and
sprinkle
over top.	Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45
minutes	or until browned and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Stir drink mix and water until dissolved.
Beat lemonade mixture and ice cream in large bowl with mixer on low until blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze until mixture mounds, if necessary.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 15 mins. or until pie can be cut easily.
Garnish with lemon slices. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, oil and eggs and mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Grate 5 squares of chocolate and add to batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured, fluted tube pan. Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; invert on wire rack and completely cool.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar. Grate 3 squares of chocolate and sprinkle on cake.
Cake may be frozen.
Serves 12.

title: cornmeal batty cakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add egg and buttermilk, stirring until smooth.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn cakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are browned.
Drain well on paper towels and serve hot. Yield:
20 small cakes.

title: salad
directions: Wash the lettuce and cut it into pieces. Cut the potatoes into cubes. Add peeled and sliced carrots. Add the cooked macaroni, drained peas and corn. Put everything in a bowl and toss with mayonnaise.

title: strawberry-orange jam
directions: Thaw berries and remove seeds and core from orange.
Grind fine.
In kettle, combine berries, orange and water.
Add pectin and mix well.
Place on high heat and stir constantly.
Bring to a rolling boil. Add sugar.
Keep stirring and heat again to high boil.
Boil hard 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Skim and stir each 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal with hot lids.
Makes 4 to 5 (8 ounce) jars.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Mix gelatine with 6 tablespoons water and add pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil; set aside to cool.
Add the rest of ingredients.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Spread batter in 9 x 5-inch baking dish.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.
Top with 12 saltines, crumbled or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini 1
directions: Cook chicken in 3 1/2 quarts of water.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Save broth.
Put cheese in broth.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Stir everything together in pot.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly. Freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add cinnamon and flour to mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar and put in 13 x 10-inch dish or pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Allow mixture to cool.

title: squash tomatillo bisque
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add squash, chilies and tomatillos and saute 5 more minutes.
Add broth and simmer for 20 minutes, until squash is tender.
Remove from heat. Add 1/2 bunch cilantro, shredded tortillas and lime juice.
Use food processor or blender and process in batches until smooth. Reheat and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with optional garnishes.
Makes 10 cups.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well. Blend flour into mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful of mixture onto greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 2 dozen cookies.
Slide cookies off with spatula onto wire rack to cool.

title: blender breakfast
directions: In blender or food processor, combine banana, milk, honey, bran and egg (if using egg); process until smooth.
Pour into tall glass.
Serves 1.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Halfway through baking, stir.

title: eggplant supper soup
directions: Heat oil & butter in 5-quart kettle over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add beef and brown.
Add garlic, carrot, celery, tomatoes with liquid, broth, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, cover and reduce heat to simmer until macaroni is tender (about 10 minutes).
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: crispy ice cream ball
directions: Combine butter, frosting and corn syrup in bowl; mix well. Stir in cereal, coat well.
Press into waxed paper-lined 10 x 15-inch pan.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread ice cream over rice mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Freeze until firm.
Thin slice from one end to the other.
Makes a tasty summer dessert.

title: frank's chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a big pot and cover with water.
Heat to simmering stage and add bay leaves, salt and pepper. Simmer until chicken is tender. Add cornstarch thickener and enough water to cover chicken well. Bring to simmering stage again.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except popcorn and baking soda.
Dissolve mixture over low heat.
Boil for 5 minutes on medium.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir and pour over popcorn, coating the corn.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: lazy perogie casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with noodles.
In medium bowl mix cottage cheese, egg and onion salt together.
Spread over noodles.
Cover with layer of noodles.
In same bowl, mix Cheddar cheese with potatoes, salt, onion salt and pepper.
Spread over noodles.
Cover with another layer of noodles.
Melt butter in pan and saute onions until transparent.
Pour over noodles.
Cover.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with sour cream.
Serves 8 generously.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: I use a very heavy stainless steel skillet to prepare this dish. Prepare ingredients by cutting the meat into cubes, and cutting the onions and peppers into strips. Preheat skillet to a hot surface and place the steak cubes onto the hot surface. I add no oil to the skillet. The beef will stick some but it will be alright! Stir the beef cubes around until brown on all sides. There is usually enough juices and oils from the meat now to add the vegetables strips to the skillet and stir fry with the beef cubes just a little. Salt the meat and vegetables to suit your taste.

Add the grape juice to the skillet, cover, reduce the heat to low and let this simmer until the meat is tender. The brown stuck to the bottom of the skillet will cook off into the juice and will make a nice gravy when you serve this beef tip dish over rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Add enchilada sauce, soups, condensed milk and green chilies.
Simmer about 10 minutes. Put Doritos in large baking dish.
Top with grated cheese after pouring meat mixture on chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: indian pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Simmer milk; remove from heat.
Combine cornmeal, molasses, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, butter, salt, baking soda, eggs and half the milk in a bowl.
Whisk thoroughly. Stir in remaining milk.
Pour into a well-greased 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake 5 to 7 hours, occasionally until firm.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; blend well.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk and pepper. In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cocoa mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in large resealable plastic bag or tightly covered container.
Stir mix before measuring.
For each serving, place 3 to 4 tablespoons of dry
mix in cup.
Fill with 1 cup boiling water; stir well. Makes about 7 cups mix; 28 to 37 (1 cup) servings.
One cup prepared cocoa, cal:
60; fat:
1 gram.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Brown onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup and broccoli; heat through.
Add cheese and rest of ingredients and serve warm. Ripple potato chips are the best for this.

title: spicy beef fajitas
directions: In nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook red and green peppers, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt until lightly browned.
Stir in cocktail vegetable juice; over high heat.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender; remove to bowl.

title: cranberry pecan bread
directions: In saucepan, combine liqueur, sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon stick. Bring to boil. Stir to dissolve sugar. Add cranberries. Reduce heat to simmer and cook until berries are about to burst, 8 minutes. Remove from heat to cool. Remove cinnamon stick and cloves. Discard.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Combine gelatin and boiling water in electric blender. Cover and blend at low speed until dissolved, 1 minute.
Add measured liquid, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Cover and blend on high speed 15 seconds.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: all-bran loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let sit for at least 1 hour.
Fold in the self-rising flour and nuts.
Put in well greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot pecan squares
directions: Cover apricots with water and boil 10 minutes; drain.
Cool. Cut in small pieces (scissors).
Cream butter and sugar; add 1 cup flour.
Pat firmly in ungreased 7 x 11-inch pan (put flour on hands).
Bake 25 minutes at 350° (light brown).
Blend eggs and brown sugar.
Add additional flour, baking powder and vanilla; blend.
Add apricots and pecans.
Spread carefully over already cooked mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Cut in bars.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Divide dough into 16 pieces; pat each into a 3-inch circle. Combine peanut butter, peanuts, honey and cinnamon.
Place a rounded teaspoon in center of each circle of dough.

Wrap dough around mixture to form a ball; pinch edges to seal. Place seam side down in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover; let rise until almost double (1 hour). Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cover with foil last 10 minutes. Cool.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cinnamon and water over medium heat until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour onto waxed paper and separate.

title: pan coater
directions: Mix ingredients into a paste and store in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.
Use with a paste brush in place of greasing and flouring pans.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Tear up meat; lay in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix in broccoli and noodles.
In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add milk and stir until thick and smooth.
Add cheese to sauce; stir until all is melted.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning and beans. Drain; set aside to cool.
Mix the lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Add beef mixture and toss.
Just before serving, add salad dressing.
Top with crushed Doritos chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and 1 cup shortening. Add the eggs, bananas, Bisquick and, if desired, the chopped walnuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Check with a toothpick in center to see if bread is dry.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: hot crab dish
directions: Mix and serve warm with taco chips.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease large casserole or lasagna pan.
Rinse and drain kraut, place on bottom of pan and add noodles.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese and corned beef, crumbled.
Add soup mixture, then buttered cubes of bread.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: raisin-orange sauce(very good with ham or duckling.)
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Place in top of double boiler or heavy saucepan over low heat.
Slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
(If lumps occur, strain.) Cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: rum baked acorn squash
directions: Place acorn squash cut side down in greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes or until squash is easily pierced.
Turn right side up and scoop out seeds.
Scoop out squash into bowl.
Reserve shells.
Mash squash and mix with pineapple, butter, bread, rum extract and brown sugar.
Spoon mixture into squash shells.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) oven for another 20 minutes or until lightly browned. This is delicious and it freezes well.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine butter, cheese, garlic salt and salt and mix well. Dip each chicken piece in mixture, reserving any left over.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cabin cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in jar with tight lid.
To use, place 1/4 cup mix in 8 ounce cup.
Fill with hot water.
Stir well.

title: hasty cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the first 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and cook sweet potatoes.
Place in buttered baking dish. Pour over potatoes the syrup made of butter, brown sugar and hot water.
Serve.

title: candied dates(uj-wee)
directions: Remove pits from dates.
Stuff each with an almond.
Press opening to close.
Roll in sugar.

title: pineapple turnovers
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add to milk, then mix into flour mixture with wooden spoon.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans and soak 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and cook beans in 2 quarts of water for 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Put in Chaurice sausage or any smoked sausage of your choice the last hour.
Cut into bite size chunks.
Serve over rice.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir to dissolve; add 1/2 cup cold water and stir.
Pour into glass baking dish and refrigerate until jelled.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Let stand while heating 2 cups of milk to boiling point.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup sugar and unflavored gelatin.
Blend well.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix until well blended and smooth.
Divide into 3 large glasses or containers of same size so that each container has the same amount.
Let cool.
Spread 1 container over lime jello in pan.
Then prepare orange jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Let cool while white layer is setting.
Alternate remainder of flavors (colors) of gelatin with white layer in between each color.
Allow each layer to set.
This takes a little time to prepare.
Looks pretty when done.
There will be seven layers, four jello and 3 milk mixtures.
End with raspberry flavor on top (not strawberry or cherry).

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients except crumbs (cut up corned beef in cubes).
Top with crumbs and butter and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mississippi recipe chicken
directions: Cook chicken halves or breasts on grill, basting often with this mixture.
Be sure to cook slowly.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Prepare dressing with eggs, sugar and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat in butter.
Let cool while cutting up fruit.
Cut fruit into large bowl.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Fold dressing into fruit.
Beat cream; fold into fruit mixture. Freeze overnight.
Serve frozen.

title: microwave cheesy tomato soup
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients; heat 12 to 15 minutes until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with seasoned croutons or small pretzel rings.

title: cheddar cheese soup(england)
directions: Cover and simmer onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes, until tender.
Stir in flour, pepper and mustard.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese; heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, just until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla (which are beaten together).
Blend well.
Divide dough in half.
Roll, between wax paper; roll size of cookie sheet.
Spread filling.
Roll other half.
Place on top of filling.
Close sides. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese and potato wild rice soup
directions: Combine rice and water in saucepan and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Fry bacon pieces and onion in skillet until bacon is crisp.
Drain bacon and onion on paper towel.
Place soup in large saucepan, dilute as directed.
Stir in 1 quart milk, bacon, onion, cheese and cooked rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk; mix for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers and pudding mix.
Layer crackers 3 times and pudding mix 2 times.
Melt icing in microwave for 1 minute and pour over the top layer (graham crackers).
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and dip mix together until creamy.
Bake pizza crust according to directions; let cool. Spread creamy mixture on top of crust.
Add vegetables on top. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and refrigerate for 20 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix milk and half and half together.
Pour 1 3/4 cups of this mixture into a heavy saucepan with 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Heat to warm point, stirring.
Mix egg yolks, 1/4 cup milk mixture and cornstarch.
Add to warm milk mixture in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into baked, cooled pie shell.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Add the 2/3 cup sugar and continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Spread over pie.
Make sure to seal the edges of the pie with meringue.
Bake in a 350° oven for a few minutes until meringue is browned.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Cool and serve.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, hot milk, eggs and rhubarb. Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with egg whites.

title: irene's creole pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops to brown lightly.
Place chops in casserole; top with onion rings, green pepper strips and garlic.
Blend sauce and pour over top.
Bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: coconut oatmeal crisps
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 4 cups hot water. Stir in sugar and a pinch of salt. When partly set, add grated pineapple and grated carrots.
Put in a pan and refrigerate to finish setting. When ready, cut into squares to serve. Can serve on lettuce with a dab of mayonnaise on top (whipped topping is also good).

title: golden tuna-rific meat ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and parsley.
Chill for 1 hour.
Place 1 cup cornflakes on wax paper and crush with rolling pin to make 1/4 cup crushed flakes.
Sprinkle with parsley and mix.
Pile tuna mixture on wax paper over crushed flakes. Shape into ball and roll over flakes until coated.
Place in center of serving platter and circle with assorted crackers. Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix. Pour into 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt the oleo; add the raw rice.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 1 hour, 15 minutes.

title: knox blocks
directions: Dissolve fruit juice and gelatine in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take pan off stove and add jello, stirring until dissolved. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into tiny squares and eat with fingers.

title: delicious cake mix cake
directions: Buy your favorite cake mix and follow the directions.
Cook 8 minutes less than the recipe calls for.
As the cake cools (before icing it), the heat from the pans will finish cooking the cake. After the cake cools, use 1 1/2 cans of commercial icing (your favorite flavor).
Undercooking the mix and using more then the usual amount of icing will make this your favorite cake.

title: granny bars
directions: Lay two layers of foil to cover bottom and sides of cookie sheet.
Lay graham crackers flat.
Put butter and sugar in micro-safe bowl.
Boil in micro for 3 to 4 minutes.
Spoon liquid onto crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 4 to 6 minutes or until bubbly.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: baked potato pizza
directions: Bake crust at 425° until browned. Spread cream cheese on cooked crust. Slice unpeeled, cooked potatoes in 1/4-inch slices. Place potatoes on top of cream cheese, spread out and not touching. Top with cheeses, bacon bits and scallions. Bake at 425° until cheese is bubbly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and garlic salt.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft stage.
Add raw peanuts. Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla, food coloring and butter.
Beat until creamy.
Drop on wax paper, 1 tablespoon per patty.

title: tangy baked fish
directions: Place flounder, sole or perch fillets in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Combine dry white wine, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over fish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until fish turns opaque, about 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: savory sauced chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in oleo until onion is tender but not brown.
Combine vegetable juice cocktail, parsley, cornstarch, marjoram and basil; stir into onion mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Arrange chicken breasts in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce mixture over chicken.
Bake, covered with foil, in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove foil; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend brown sugar and flour.
Add water, then milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked crust and top with egg white meringue.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Combine Jell-O and 1 cup boiling water. Stir 2 minutes, add cold
water.
Chill
until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Fold
in
yogurt
and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: flank steak and green beans
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut across grain into quarter-inch strips; then cut strips into 2-inch lengths.
Combine soy sauce, sugar and cornstarch; blend well.
Pour over steak.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Heat oil and add steak strips. Cook, tossing to brown on all sides, about 3 minutes.
Remove steak from pan and add green beans and reserved marinade.
Add water. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Add steak.
Serves 6. (This is a good low fat, low calorie main dish.)

title: apple pudding
directions: Pare, core and slice apples into deep casserole.
Mix together lemon juice, water, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of the sugar; add to the apples.
Combine remaining sugar with flour and salt; work in the butter.
Sprinkle this over apples.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes or until apples are tender and the crust is crisp and golden brown.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef in large skillet until lightly browned and drain. Add all ingredients except cheese.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain the fat and rinse meat.
Follow directions on chili package.

title: lemon barbecue shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; place in a large shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.
Thread shrimp onto skewers.
Broil or grill 5 to 6 inches from medium heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with marinade.
Yields 6 servings (about 139 calories per serving).

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix well and shape in balls.
Roll in crushed corn frosted flakes.
Put on cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend all the ingredients together with plastic spatula until well blended.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Cover the oatmeal with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Cream together sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternating with oatmeal.
Stir in half the chocolate chips.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in the batter and sprinkle with remaining chips; add the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix next three ingredients together and place on top of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Melt chocolate in microwave.
Spread on top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Stir all ingredients until dissolved.
Beat until smooth.
It will be thin but thickens later on.
Can be done in a blender. Makes 1 quart.

title: cucumber-lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool until partially set. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: small cocktail franks
directions: Cook franks (boil).
In a small pot, whisk together the French's mustard and black currant jelly.
Heat until well blended.
Serve over the franks.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in 2-quart casserole; add white sauce. Brown chops; season and arrange over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done and chops are tender.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Tear bread slices into small pieces and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour over bread and stir with a fork until ingredients are smoothly blended.
Set baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If you wish, you may add 1/2 cup raisins before baking or place 2 slices apples on top and sprinkle with a little sugar and cinnamon before baking.

title: church punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice with sherbet in punch bowl. Add 7-Up right before serving.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in an 8-inch square baking pan or casserole. Toss bread cubes in melted margarine and sprinkle over top of ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix egg yolks, oil and milk together, then blend into dry ingredients.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Makes 4 waffles.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs; cream.
Add flour and baking powder; cream well.
Add milk, lemon and vanilla extract.
Beat the mixture for 2 minutes.
Preheat oven.
Grease tube pan with Crisco; flour lightly.
Bake at 290° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: twinkle banana fluff
directions: Split Twinkies long ways.
Put in 13 x 9-inch glass pan with filling up.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Cover bananas with crushed pineapple.
Mix cream cheese with confectioners sugar and put on top of pineapple.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk then fold in whipped topping.
Pour on top of cream cheese.
Mix 3 ounces cream cheese with 2 tablespoons milk and 3 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Drizzle on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: albert's cake
directions: Mix salt, soda and water in small cup.
Add to remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserolegroves, texas
directions: Line a 9 X 13 pan with foil.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into lined pan.
Seal with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Add boiling chicken broth to lemon jello and stir well. Dissolve gelatine in cold water; add to first mixture and mix well.
Whisk mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Whisk into jello mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add to pan in following order:

title: diet salad
directions: Mix orange sections with cottage cheese and Cool Whip, then add orange Jell-O.
Stir well and chill.

title: chicken in tomato cream(serves 4)
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet; add onion and thighs.
Cook until thighs are golden brown, turning once. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes with liquid, basil, salt and zucchini. Cover and cook over medium heat 40 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to heated plate.
Stir sour cream into sauce and pour over chicken.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size chunks.
Roll in flour and fry in oil.
Place in crock-pot on low to keep warm.
Heat broth in saucepan.
Add soy sauce and use cornstarch (or the flour and water) to thicken.
When thickened, add to chicken.
Add green onions and if serving immediately, add cashews.
If not, wait until ready to serve because they may get "soggy."
