title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix all other ingredients together (except cheese and crackers) and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Cook until bubbling. Let bubble about 45 seconds.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal. Pour into buttered brownie mix.

title: chicken-n-fried rice
directions: Fry cooked chicken in a little butter or oil.
Add broccoli and cook 20 minutes.
In separate pan, saute mushrooms in oil or butter.
Add to broccoli along with 2 cups cooked rice.
Heat through; serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts, applesauce and mixed dry ingredients.
Turn into a buttered loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased), 2 inches apart.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: rice dessert
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into tiny pieces.
Stir in bacon.
Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together. Stir until smooth.
Just before serving salad, add red onion and cheese.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over salad.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Cut each slice of bacon in half.
Wrap chestnuts with bacon. Secure with toothpick.
Bake on broiler rack in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked cucumbers
directions: Parboil sliced cucumbers for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain.
Put cucumbers in shallow dish.
Add grated sharp cheese.
Mix.
Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of cucumbers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top when serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix together the soup, vegetables and chicken and place in casserole dish.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Simmer all ingredients until done (15 to 20 minutes).

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot by the fire or in the warmth of your family and friends.

title: marie's chocolate pie
directions: Cook and stir with wooden spoon.
Pour into baked pie shell. Whip egg whites with cream of tartar and sugar for meringue. Lightly brown meringue in oven.
Can top with Cool Whip.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in flour. Add remaining ingredients, except the crab and bread crumbs. Return to heat and stir until sauce thickens some.
Then stir in the crab.
Remove from heat, pour into greased baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 400° oven (1-quart baking dish).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into square baking dish.

title: crabmeat-rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan. Add onion, pepper and celery. Saute until lightly browned, about 10 minutes. Add rest of ingredients, except crabmeat. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add crabmeat and cook for 3 to 5 minutes longer.
(If thinner consistency is desired, add 1 cup tomato juice.) Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 4 tablespoons butter until tender. Mix with pimientos.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of the onions, half of the cheese and half of the crackers.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.
Add half and half and salt to the beaten eggs.
Pour egg mixture over casserole.
Mix remaining cracker crumbs with 1 tablespoon melted butter and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mash peaches well and mix with jello and heat so jello will dissolve.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Put in refrigerator until almost jelled; fold in Cool Whip and put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
When firm, cut into squares.
Other fruit may be substituted for the peaches. Sugar-free jello may also be substituted.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together. Beat 4 minutes.
Put in 2 greased bread tins and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: salsa pronto
directions: Place tomatoes in blender. Cover and run on lowest speed 2 seconds to chop tomatoes. Combine with onions, cilantro, lemon juice, garlic and pepper sauce. Add additional pepper sauce if desired. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain juice from the pineapple completely.
In a small mixing bowl, mix the pineapple with cream cheese.
It is messy, but mixes best if done by hand.
Once thoroughly mixed, form a ball on wax paper.
Let ball chill for 30 minutes to 1 hour to make a little more solid.
Once chilled, roll cheese ball in pecans until completely covered.
Serve with any crackers.

title: spicy frankfurters
directions: Halve franks lengthwise; place in skillet.
Blend flour with 2 tablespoons water; add remaining water, ketchup, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over franks.
Cover, simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place stewed chicken breasts in the bottom of a lightly greased baking dish.
Top with broccoli.
Melt margarine over low heat in a small saucepan.
Add soup, milk and sour cream.
Cook over low heat just until warmed.
Pour sauce over broccoli layer. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cole farms salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Store in salad dressing container in refrigerator.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Place pork in heavy pan.
In a bowl, combine tomatoes, vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and sugar. Pour over meat and bake for 5 minutes at 300°.
Remove bone from roast.
Shred the meat with a fork.
Set meat aside.
Add Tabasco sauce and salt to liquid to taste.
Cook down if too much liquid.
Serve on buns.

title: mammaw steenbergen's best biscuits
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Combine lard with flour. Add milk/soda mixture. Stir.
Put on floured board and knead lightly until smooth.
Pat out and cut.
Bake in a 450° oven until lightly brown.

title: ashville salad
directions: Heat
soup; add gelatin that has soaked in 1/2 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, cheese, onion, celery, pepper, salt
and mayonnaise.
Pour into mold and chill.
Add tuna, crab or ham for luncheon.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Stir together cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Set aside. Combine soup, broccoli, celery, milk, onion, seasonings and chicken.
Set aside.
Place 2 raw lasagna noodles in greased loaf pan.
Layer with 1/2 cheese mix and 1/3 soup mix.
Repeat twice. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar.
Slowly pour boiling water around edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: paula's pineapple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Thin with pineapple juice if needed. Serve with crackers.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon cubes, carrots, potatoes, celery, onions, parsley, salt and pepper in large pot.
Cook over medium heat for 40 minutes; add milk and butter and cook another 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
This is a very easy and economical recipe. Serve with homemade bread.

title: breakfast salsa
directions: Combine all in a bowl and season to taste with salt and pepper. Makes 2 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda and popcorn, in 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Bring to a boil, then cook on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.

title: raspberry lemon muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs, milk, vegetable oil and lemon extract.
Stir egg mixture into dry mixture just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with 4 strips of bacon, cut in half.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes until bacon is crisp.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and shortening in a large mixing bowl until fluffy. Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Cream well after each addition. Stir in vanilla, lemon extract and lemon juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.

title: french meat pie
directions: Simmer beef and pork in large frypan.
Peel onion and dice. Dice celery.
Add onion and celery to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer until the liquid is almost all absorbed.
Add the package of potatoes or 1/2 cup of mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and spices.
Cool overnight.
Stir before using.
Place filling in a 10 inch pie crust.
Cover top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned.
Serves 6-8.

title: fruit crumb bars
directions: In mixing bowl, stir flour, oats, sugar and soda.
Stir in margarine.
Spread 2 cups of mixture in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Stir peel into pie filling.
Carefully spread on top of crust.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until top is golden.
Cool in pan.
Drizzle icing over.
Cut into bars.
Good plain, better with icing.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper and spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Add cake mixture.
Combine cream cheese and oleo; add powdered sugar. Drop mixture on top of cake using big spoon.
Do not spread.
Put about 6 spoonfuls until topping is used up.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.
When cake is cool, turn over and remove wax paper.
Coconut will be on top.
May serve with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish. Cover with topping and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: very good salad dressing
directions: Mix together in blender.
Great as a vegetable dip or salad dressing.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until
light
and
foamy.
Beat
in
sugar,
vanilla and butter, until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add
to
egg mixture.
Mix
at	low speed until well blended. Stir in nuts (mixture will be stiff).
Spread evenly into pan. Bake at
350° for
to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen.

title: cut green bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter; add flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add milk (stirring constantly); cook until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Add beans.
Layer mixture with Swiss cheese in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into eighths.
Place in a large baking dish, skin side down.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Saute onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour ingredients over chicken and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn skin side up.
Bake 20 minutes, basting frequently.

title: happiness pudding
directions: If prepared carefully and served daily, this will be your favorite recipe.
Generously serves one family no matter the size.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Add dressing mix.
Chill and shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add chopped vegetables, stirring to coat with flour.
Stir in cheese, then blend in eggs and milk.
Pour into greased muffin pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peach delight pie
directions: Mix together and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan the self-rising flour, nuts and butter; cook until light brown.
Let cool.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Gently boil water and carefully place eggs in pan.
Boil 10 to 12 minutes steadily.
Remove immediately and put in cold water. Peel while still warm.
Slice eggs in half, remove egg yolks. Mix together yolks, mayonnaise, mustard, pickles, salt and pepper. Place this mixture into egg whites, serve or refrigerate.

title: thick cut o rings and spicy dipping sauce
directions: Heat 1 inch oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cut onions across into 1 inch rings and separate. Discard the outer layer of skin on your rings. Pour evaporated milk into a small bowl. Mix flour with seasonings in a shallow dish. Dip individual rings in milk, then coat in flour. And repeat for a double dip. Fry in a single layer in hot oil until golden brown. Remove to paper bag or towel lined surface to drain. Salt while hot, to your taste.

title: lemon cream dressing
directions: Fold the whipped cream into the mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in lemon rind and juice.
Season well and add mustard to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon water to thin the dressing if necessary.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: beefy chicken
directions: Salt chicken; set aside.
Melt margarine; add rice, onion and soup.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Lay chicken on top of mixture, pushing down into liquid.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pork chops spadaro
directions: Heat oil in skillet and add pork chops.
Brown well.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onion, rosemary and chicken broth. Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: prozona kapusta(stewed cabbage)
directions: Slice or chop cabbage; scald and drain.
Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Put cabbage and onions in roaster.
In pan, put 1 cup water, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Add this to cabbage in roaster and stir.
Cook about 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Cut a link of kielbasa in slices and add to cabbage. Cook until tender, 45 minutes, at 350°.
Watch liquids in roaster. Should not be too soupy, so it is roasting to slightly brown. When done, make a roux of flour and water.
Add a little at a time to a nice consistency.
Add mushrooms if desired.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pizza beef loaf
directions: Mix beef, egg, crackers and onion.
In separate dish, mix the remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture, saving enough to pour some over top.
Form into loaf and cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix.
Fry
in
oil in frying pan, until golden brown on both sides.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir the sugar, flour and cinnamon together.
Add the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Next, add the zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased/Pam loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except gravy.
Shape into oblong patties. Brown in skillet; drain fat.
Add gravy.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley (optional).

title: heavenly roast and gravy
directions: Spread flour in bottom of cooking bag.
Put roast in the bag. Add potatoes, onion and carrots.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Add water to bag and seal.
Punch a few holes in top of bag to prevent an explosion.
Cook on 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: mediterranean shrimp
directions: Add olive oil or olive oil spray to large saucepan.
Over medium heat, saut onions, garlic and celery until onion is translucent.
Add chicken broth for more liquid.
Add oregano; cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomato, shrimp and cooked spaghetti. Mix until all shrimp and spaghetti is covered with vegetable mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: lima beans
directions: Partially cook salt pork covered with water. Drain if water is salty.
Add more hot water. Set aside.
Soak limas for about 10 minutes.
Heat until boiling; turn off heat.
Combine salt pork and limas. Add seasonings, celery, onion and garlic. Cook until tender.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer broccoli, mushroom soup and chicken on top of rice.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: pin wheels
directions: Mix with mixer or food processor.
Spread mixture on soft floured tortilla shells.
Roll up shells, place in refrigerator until chilled.
Cut 1/2 inch slice pin wheels.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix in a large punch bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil large kettle of water; place cabbage in water for about 3 minutes or until limp.
Drain.
Combine egg, milk, onion, salt, pepper, beef and cooked rice.
Place about 1/4 cup meat mixture in each leaf; fold in sides and roll ends over meat.
Fasten with a toothpick.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix well cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries, nuts and bananas.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex and freeze.
Remove 15 to 20 minutes before meal. Serve on bed of lettuce as a salad or plain as a dessert.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add the next 3 ingredients and top with grated cheese.

title: caramel crisps
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Cover with whole graham crackers.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, coconut and almonds evenly. Over medium heat, combine sugar, butter, cinnamon and vanilla. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar is well blended
(4 to 5 minutes).
Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: party bread spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Serve spread on party rye bread or crackers.
Garnish with olive slices, if desired. Yields about 2 cups.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 dessert
directions: Mix together flour, pecans and melted margarine.
Mix well and pat down in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: frozen cranberry salad(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Mix well and freeze. Take out 10 minutes before serving and slice.

title: sausage-broccoli casserole
directions: Brown sausage, then slice.
Butter 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, beat 6 eggs, adding 6 teaspoons of milk, 1/2 cup onions and salt.
Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place a 24 x 18-inch piece of heavy duty aluminum foil in a baking pan.
Place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix.
Spread on meat.
Top with vegetables.
Fold over foil and seal securely.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco mix, water and olives.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Place dinner rolls around a greased pie pan, to make a crust.
Add a layer of crushed Fritos, then add hamburger mixture.
Spoon on sour cream.
Add Cheddar cheese and a layer of crushed Fritos on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: celery kraut salad
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar; heat until sugar is dissolved. Let cool. Pour mixture over vegetables. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes over low heat.
Add margarine; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: banana splush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-up.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Take from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Chop into pieces and add 7-up (1 litre or more) to make into a slushy consistency.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and well beaten egg.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add them to mixture, a little at a time, alternating with the milk until all are mixed.
Roll 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into cakes and bake at 350° until done.

title: tropical healthy fruit soup
directions: Put as many cups of fruit at a time as the blender will hold, adding nutmeg and extract as you go.
Puree until smooth.
You can freeze fruit first if you want soup to be really cold.
Fruit soup can be as thick as bisque by combining puree with buttermilk, sour cream (light) or yogurt.

Use a quarter to half the amount of fruit puree or you can make fruit consume without dairy products and thinning it with sparkling water, tea, cranberry or orange juice. You can also add pieces of whole fruit to the soup.
Either version can be poured over ice cream, frozen yogurt or sherbet.

title: sherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pecans) in mixing bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour Hot Sherry Glaze over cake.

title: old bay seasoned fried or baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except oil.
Rinse chicken well and flour.
Let sit for 5 minutes while heating oil in frying pan. Before frying chicken, flour it again, using all or most of flour mixture.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish with broccoli on bottom then chicken. Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over broccoli and chicken. Melt butter and blend with bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate lovers pizza
directions: Microwave all but 1/3 cup vanilla morsels together for 2 minutes.
Add peanuts, Rice Krispies, marshmallows and coconut. Mix into melted morsels.
Press mixture onto a lightly greased 16-inch pizza pan.
Melt remaining vanilla morsels and 1 teaspoon oil.
Drizzle over top.
Place cherry halves and gummy fish on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and put in freezer for 15 minutes. Insert in pizza box and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off grease.
Add seasonings, Ro-Tel tomatoes and water.
Stir well and add remaining ingredients.
Do not drain the vegetables before adding. Cook about an hour or cook in crock-pot for several hours.
If you like it a little hotter, add an extra can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put 1/2 lettuce in a bowl.
Layer on top onions, peas, sugar and mayonnaise.
Cover with rest of lettuce and cheese, then bacon bits.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Mix and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix corned beef, cheeses, soup, onion and milk.
Stir in cooked noodles and pour in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper; roll in flour. Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet; brown chicken pieces and place in roaster.
Add broth to pan juices.
Scrape browned bits from bottom and sides of skillet; pour over chicken.
Saute onion, parsley and mushrooms in remaining butter.
Pour vegetable mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove chicken to warm platter; stir mustard and half and half into liquid in roaster and heat.
Pour sauce over chicken on platter. (Mustard and half and half may also be stirred into onion, parsley, mushroom and liquid and baked as directed.)
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit squares
directions: Spread pecans in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar; mix in flour, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Sprinkle fruit over all.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Batter will look soft.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mayo, cheese, parsley and hot pepper sauce in medium size bowl until well blended.
Fold in artichokes. Spoon into ungreased 2-cup ovenproof dish.
Bake for 20 minutes until bubbly.
Spread on crackers or thinly sliced, toasted French bread.

title: moist nut bread
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy the butter and sugar. Add well-beaten eggs and stir until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Add almond and vanilla extracts.
Stir in chopped nut meats.
A combination of hickory nuts and pecans and perhaps a few English walnuts.
Be sure to remember to chop some very fine, leaving rest coarsely chopped.
Pour into a well-greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle top of loaf with a few additional nuts. Let stand 20 minutes, then bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: picnic delight
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Add 1 cup sugar; mix well.
Add egg; beat 1 minute. Combine buttermilk and vanilla; add alternately with dry ingredients to the cream mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and nuts. Sprinkle over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and corn syrup, microwave 7 - 9 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla, mix quickly and cook 2 - 3 minutes longer. Add soda and stir until mixture is foamy. Pour immediately onto a greased baking sheet.

title: fajitas
directions: Season each side of flank steak well with Tony's seasoning, black pepper and garlic powder.

title: sweet potatoes(dark yams)
directions: Peel and cut yams into chunks.
Place all ingredients in Dutch oven pan with lip.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil; add peppers.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick. Place in jars and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. For low-fat, omit oil.
Remove seeds from tomatoes for seedless sauce.

title: peanut butter dippers
directions: To assemble, spread about 1 teaspoon peanut butter over flat side of 1 vanilla wafer; press end of wooden stick into peanut butter and top with a plain vanilla wafer making a sandwich.
Melt candy coating in a small saucepan over low heat.
Dip cookies into coating allowing excess to drip off.
Place on wax paper upright until cool.

title: sweet potato biscuits(makes 3 dozen drop biscuits.)
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, sugar, milk and salt. Mix thoroughly. In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and cinnamon together. Add to potato mixture. Drop onto cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix sausage and cheese spread.
Put on muffins.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked apples
directions: Using small knife, score apples around middle to prevent skin from splitting during cooking.
Place apples in casserole (8-cup) and sprinkle remaining ingredients over.
Cover and microwave 9 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1 stick butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Mix and pat in pan.

title: fudge
directions: Mix; bring to boil.
Turn to low temperature and cook for about 15 minutes (hard ball stage).
Remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring, butter and chopped pecans.
Beat until stiff.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Step 1:
Peel and slice cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices (cored).

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Recipe may be doubled.

title: pork 'n bean surprise
directions: Slice hot dogs and Portuguese sausage diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Slice each bacon into 7 to 8 pieces.
In glass casserole, mix beans, water, ketchup, mustard, sugar and pepper.
Add hot dogs, sausage and bacon.
Stir to mix; cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Boil chicken
until
tender, remove skin and chip meat. Grate cheese.
Put small amounts of chicken and cheese on wide end of crescent
rolls; salt and pepper to taste.	Roll up and fold ends over.
Mix	soup
and milk; pour in casserole dish. Place rolls in sauce and bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Have meat ground extra fine, together.
Combine egg with beer and bread crumbs; let stand 10 minutes.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter, until tender but not brown.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Shape into small balls, using about 1 tablespoon mixture for each.
Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter; brown thoroughly on all sides, shaking pan frequently to keep balls round.
When meat is brown, reduce heat and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Put into fondue with gravy.

title: cottage cheese and beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown meat until brown and drain. Add tomato sauce, oregano and heat.
Place 1/2 noodles in shallow baking dish.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, and green onions and spread on noodles.
Add remaining noodles.
Pour meat mixture over top.
Bake at 350 about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: al pesto spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients, except spaghetti, in a bowl.
Set aside. Cook pasta following package instructions.
Drain.

title: chicken-cheese canapes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise and scallions. Blend in basil, thyme and pepper.
Add Swiss cheese and 2 tablespoons Parmesan; blend well.
Spread chicken mixture over English muffin halves, dividing evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Arrange on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes until lightly browned on top.
Cut muffins into quarters. Serve hot.

title: sesame pasta salad
directions: Prepare fresh or dry pasta (e.g. linguine).
Cut chicken in bite-size pieces and saute.
Prepare snow peas, sugar snaps or asparagus tips (just blanch crisp-tender).
Cut onions, diagonally, into 1-inch pieces.

title: pavlova
directions: Whisk egg whites until stiff.
Whisk in sugar slowly.
Beat on high speed until mixture is glossy.
Add vinegar and fold in cornstarch.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Switch off oven and leave to cool in oven.
Place mixture on baking parchment or greaseproof paper.
Bake on ovenproof plate or in a tin.
Fill with cream and strawberries.
Enjoy!

title: baba's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add sugar and milk.

Pour batter into pan on top of butter. Warm the fruit and juice. Spread over batter. Bake at 350° until light brown (but not too brown), approximately 35 to 40 minutes on middle rack. Crust will come to the top. Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil and peel shrimp (frozen cooked salad shrimp).
Mix all other ingredients together and combine with shrimp.

title: tomato pie
directions: Fill pie shell with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil, chives and green onions.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese. Spread over tomatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(this cake is made in an electric pan.)
directions: Mix in a separate bowl.
Mix well and pour over pineapple. Turn heat up to 350° and bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: bacon and eggs du jour
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon butter. Add soup. Gradually stir in milk and heat.
Add remaining butter to water. Heat until butter is melted.
Combine hot liquid with bread stuffing mix.
Arrange 1/3 of stuffing in a buttered 2-quart casserole. Top with half the egg sections and 1/3 of soup mixture. Repeat, using all the eggs. Top with remaining stuffing and soup mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Pour cold eggnog into bowl.
Add pie filling mix, rum and nutmeg.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in 2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg, if desired.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: ham and egg brunch
directions: Put bread and ham in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with cheese, then pour milk, eggs, salt and mustard on bread mix.
Top with butter.
Cover overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: bessie's raisin biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick with milk.
Add sugar, cinnamon, raisins and salt.
Knead gently.
Roll on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and milk.
While biscuits are still warm, spread on biscuits.

title: barbecued tuna burgers(weight watchers only)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls, in a nonstick skillet. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon barbecued tuna, evenly divided, over cut rolls.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and sugar. Put in a big bowl.
Make a well in the middle of all the dry ingredients.
Add strawberries with juice, eggs, oil and pecans. Stir it all up and put in pan.
Grease and flour one cake pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: spicy pumpkin cookies
directions: In extra large mixing bowl, mix together shortening and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add pumpkin and egg, beat until combined.
In another bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat into pumpkin mixture until combined.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until top seems firm. Remove and cool.
Prepare Cookie Glaze.
Spread over cookies. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Yields 42 to 48 cookies.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and water together.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by using a tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar into stiff peaks.
Add nutmeats and chocolate bits.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Put in a 450° oven, turn off heat and leave overnight.

title: jambalaya
directions: In greased 3-quart casserole, carefully combine vegetables, undiluted soups, rice and seasonings.
Fold in raw shrimp and uncooked ground beef, which has been crumbled with fingers.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks and jam.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Beat vigorously after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 325° until done.
May use three 9-inch layer pans and frost.

title: peep potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt stick of butter.
Put potatoes in dish and add the broth. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, egg and milk.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: croatian casserole
directions: Heat oil; add beef and brown on all sides.
Pour off fat and turn beef and drippings into large casserole.
Peel onions and quarter; slice tomatoes and green pepper and add to meat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add celery, eggplant and zucchini.
Sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes longer. Makes 6 generous servings.
Serve over rice, noodles, etc.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cream together sugar and oleo. Add beaten eggs to sugar and oleo mixture and then add to bran mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture with raisins and nuts only until dry ingredients are damp.
Fill muffin pans about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
May cut recipe in half.
Freezes well.
Warm in microwave 10 to 15 seconds.

title: bar-b-q beef
directions: Sear roast at 400° 1/2 hour to brown.
Mix all remaining ingredients and cook 45 minutes.
Pour over seared roast.
Bake slow and covered until meat shreds, about 3 1/2 hours. Take meat out of pan. Cool enough to handle.
Shred meat into large bowl. Pour sauce from pan over meat and mix.
Reheat as needed.
Serve in hamburger buns.

title: quick walnut butterscotch fudge
directions: Melt morsels in microwave.
Add salt and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen pieces of candy.

title: sole franciscan
directions: Saute sole fillets in 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add rest of butter, leeks, garlic and artichoke hearts.
Saute until leeks are limp.
Add tomatoes and white wine.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top fish with sauce.

title: pickled crab apples
directions: Put cinnamon, cloves, mace and allspice in cheesecloth bag. Put water, sugar and vinegar in a kettle; heat and add bag. Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add apples; heat slowly (don't burst the apple skins).
Set overnight in syrup.
Remove bag.
Pack in jars.
Seal.
Process in boiling bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 pints: 16 to 20 apples in each.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together the chicken pieces, grapes and apple.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: light brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in brown sugar.
Let cool.
Stir in eggs, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in moderate oven for about 25 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Slice onion on top of roast.
Add water to middle of roast. Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Cool and chill.
Remove solidified fat.
Slice beef thin.
Add liquid and seasonings. Cook 3 to 4 hours over low heat.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in a flat pan.
Sprinkle onion salt, celery salt, garlic salt and liquid smoke over it.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Take brisket out of marinade.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours in covered roaster.
Slice.
Add barbecue sauce and bake 1 more hour.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add boiling water slowly to the meal and melted shortening; beat until smooth.
Add the milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.'

title: the best orange date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in sugar, egg, flour mixture, orange peel, dates and pecans. Mix well after each addition.
Spread batter into prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and edges begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely on wire rack. Frost with Orange Cream Cheese Icing.
Store, covered, in refrigerator. Cookies freeze well.
Makes 36 (1 x 3-inch) bars.

title: peanut butter hershey kiss cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Chill dough, then roll into medium size balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and place unwrapped Hershey's Kiss in center of cookie.
Place back in oven for about 45 seconds to set.
Makes 48 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O by package directions. When it is half congealed, add other ingredients. Top with Cool Whip and grated cheese.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Hush, drain and slice strawberries, then add sugar to sweeten. Slice cake into 3 layers.
Cover each layer with glaze and berries.
Add Cool Whip to layers and sides.
Decorate top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Combine beef with rice-vermicelli portion of Rice-A-Roni and eggs.
Shape into 16 medium meatballs and brown on all sides in oil.
Add 2 1/2 cups water; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Mix flavor packet of Rice-A-Roni with 2 cups water.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer additional 10 to 15 minutes, turning once.
When serving, pour brown gravy over meatballs.

title: bean and taco salad
directions: Cook beef and drain; chop onion, lettuce and tomatoes.
Grate cheese.
Drain beans.
Mix all together.
Pour on dressing.
Serve over chips.

title: coconut pies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pie shells) and mix well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: skillet rib-eye steaks
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and the seasonings in skillet.
When onion is tender, place steaks in skillet, covering them with the onions and mushrooms.
Cook steaks on medium heat as desired.

title: mints
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then add water.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Mix well.
Roll in small balls the size of a marble.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Press sugared ball in mold. Unmold at once on waxed paper.
Let dry.

title: double apple turnovers
directions: ected.
Combine apples, applesauce, sugar, cinnamon, mace and raisins in a small bowl.
Mix with a fork.
Divide dough in half. Keep one-half refrigerated until ready to use.
Roll out the other half on a lightly floured surface to a 15 x 10-inch rectangle; trim edges evenly with a pastry wheel or sharp knife.
Cut into 6 (5-inch) squares.
Place about 2 tablespoons filling on each square; moisten edges with water.
Fold over to make triangles. Crimp edges with a fork to seal.
Lift onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Repeat with remaining pastry and filling.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Serve over 8 ounces softened cream cheese with butter crackers.

title: orange fruitcake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake in a Bundt or angel food pan for 2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Simmer chicken, water, onion, salt, pepper, parsley, marjoram and bouillon 1 hour.
Add celery, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 1/2 hour more.
Cut chicken from bones.
Skim excess fat from soup.

title: extra good biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in egg and milk.
Knead a few times.
Pat out dough and cut to size desired. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bonnie kress' hawaii-pu-pu
directions: Cut 1 pound of bacon in half; roll each 1/2 strip of bacon with 1 water chestnut and stick with toothpick.
Mix sugar and ketchup and dip.
Put on pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes (and turn over halfway if you want).

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Stir for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each quarter into sugar and cinnamon combination and coat well. Put in greased cake pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix margarine and brown sugar over heat until melted.
Add nuts.
Pour over cake.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan and then dump out.
Pull off biscuit quarters and eat.
Good breakfast or coffee treat.

title: complete dinner for 10
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix together other ingredients with hamburger.
Put in large greased casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes; add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: senator's soup(navy bean)
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight (at least 6 hours).
In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove to a dish; leave fat in skillet.
To the fat, add celery and onion; cook to tender stage. Place beans and all other ingredients in slow cooker or Dutch oven.
Add 6 cups water.
Cook until beans are tender, about 5 hours.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: To the potatoes, add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Each layer should be about 1/2-inch.
Layer in round casserole dish: mashed potatoes, margarine, sour cream, bacon bits, chives and Velveeta.
Repeat until ingredients are gone, always ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marshall field ozark pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
On a piece of waxed paper, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg and sugar until light and creamy.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Turn into casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water, remove from heat.
Add stuffing, egg and sausage.
Chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape into pieces the size of pecans.
Divide bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap around mixture and secure with toothpicks.
Bake in shallow pan for 35 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Yields 30.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion, chicken broth, carrots, potatoes, green beans, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Heat to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of this into an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill until firm, then spread sour cream on top.
Add the other 1/2 of the Jell-O and chill until firm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, combine 1/3 cup mix with 1 cup water.

title: turkey chili
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, olive oil and garlic in a microwave dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent on one side. Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover and microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir once during cooking time.

title: kahlua ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream enough to mix together.
Add Heath bars and Kahlua.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Top with hot fudge sauce when serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients except cornflakes and Parmesan cheese.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour mixture into baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract while whipping cream.
Whip cream until it is thick and forms peaks.
Then take one cookie at a time and add cream and continue to stack cookies and cream into a log shape.
Then cover the entire log with whipped cream and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Cookies will soften and it makes a delicious light tasting dessert.

title: lemon cheese
directions: Cook all ingredients on top of double boiler until thick.

title: chicken rosemary(low-fat)
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
In medium skillet over medium heat, brown chicken on both sides in margarine and oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix half the cake mix (dry), margarine, sugar, water and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
Heat frosting in 1-quart saucepan until thin.
Drizzle over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely.

title: beet and nut jellied salad
directions: Drain beets and pineapple.
Heat lemon juice, vinegar and sugar.
Dissolve Jell-O in this mixture.
Add beets, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into oiled pan and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli by directions on box and place spears in dish.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise, cheese and onion; spread on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with dressing; bake 5 more minutes.

title: beef hash over rice
directions: Simmer together about 15 minutes (until onion is cooked) in a frying pan.
Add 1 package Sweet 'N Low (or 1 teaspoon sugar). Add seasoning to taste (salt, pepper and herbs).
Add 1 slice of bread (or cold biscuit, etc.).
Crumble finely and stir to thicken hash.
If too thick, add small amount of water. Serve over hot buttered rice.

title: pouleta sa creme
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and brown in half the butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cook mushrooms in remaining half of butter.
Add whipping cream, sherry and tarragon.
Simmer until consistency is like medium-thick gravy (flour can be used to thicken).
Serve over bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Add hot water to lemon jello.
Add 7-Up and cool.
Add cut up bananas, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Reserve pineapple juice.
Refrigerate to set.
Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice. Cook until thick.
Cool, then fold in whipped cream.
Spread over set jello.

title: modeling clay
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low heat for about 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
When the mixture forms a ball, remove from heat.
After the mixture cools, store in an airtight container.
Do not refrigerate.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a saucepan; stir in the flour and gradually blend in the cream.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Beat the egg yolks lightly and add with the salt, mustard, cayenne, corn, Worcestershire sauce and parsley.
Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into corn mixture. Turn into a greased casserole.
Top with the crumbs and bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a hot, greased frying pan.
Cook for about 30 minutes on low heat until potatoes are soft.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice squash and onions into a casserole dish.
Dot with oleo and add water to prevent sticking.
Bake, covered, until tender. Mix Ritz cracker crumbs, tomato sauce, melted oleo and curry powder.
Spoon on top of squash.
Poke into the squash a little so some stays on top.
Cook until bubbling and brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; take off bone.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Dilute soup with broth.
Put all but 1 cup crumbs in 9-inch square dish.
Top with chopped chicken.
Pour soup and broth over.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: festive marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour over beef, poultry or fish.
Marinate 24 hours.
Makes 7 cups.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and beat in brown sugar.
Grease bottom of long cake pan with squeeze margarine.
Pour large can of crushed pineapple with juice and the previous mixture into bottom of cake pan.
Mix butter cake mix as directed and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn over onto a long cookie sheet (so that pineapple is on top) shortly after taking out of oven. Serve while warm.

title: chili beef skillet
directions: Brown meat and onion in electric skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans, rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, 3/4 cup water and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes; stir often.
Add cheese.
Cover until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: blue ribbon bell peppers
directions: In large skillet, brown meat, onion, salt and pepper; add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce and uncooked rice.
Cover & simmer for 15 minutes.
Core and boil bell peppers for 4 minutes in salt water; place in casserole dish.
After rice mixture has simmered, stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: fried squash surprise
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces; coat well with cornmeal.
Fry squash, onion and green peppers in skillet in hot fat until squash is golden brown.

title: pink salad
directions: Bring pineapple and the juice to a boil, stir in jello.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and Dream Whip whipped.
Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then add sour cream.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°, then use toothpick for tester.

title: vegetable oil pastry
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg white, oil and water.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape into a ball. Place between 2 sheets of wax paper; roll into a 12-inch circle. Place in 9-inch pie plate; flute edges.
Prick bottom and side of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
1 pastry shell.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in bowl.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Mash this thick batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Two to three minutes before removing from oven, mix last 3 ingredients. Bring to boil.
Pour over cake that has been punched full of holes with toothpick.
Return cake to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: stew and corn bread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Empty beef stew into shallow baking dish.
In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add oil, milk and cornmeal; mix thoroughly.
Stir in cheese and green pepper or onions.
Pour batter over stew.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl until blended.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix crust ingredients and press into greased pan.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Marinate 24 hours.
Put into jars.
Freeze, less 1-inch headspace.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Whisk in the water.
Stir cornstarch over heat until thickened and clear. Remove from heat and stir in butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.

title: elizabeth's fork cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Chill for an hour or so.
Pinch off dough and shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet and press flat.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn flake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add 4 cups corn flakes, mixing well.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut while warm into bars.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pour in water.
Work flour, shortening and brown sugar together and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine macaroni, butter, cheese and seasonings.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika or butter crumbs.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: skillet bread
directions: This bread
is	cooked	on
top
of the stove.	Arrange bacon in	bottom	of
pan.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in milk
quickly.
Pour the the dough over the bacon and spread evenly.
Put
lid
on
skillet and cook slowly about 10 minutes. Pour
off
any excess fat.	Turn bread over and cook another 10 minutes.

title: pie crust(two double crust pies)
directions: Work shortening into flour until the texture is like corn meal.
Add salt and water.
Work until it is a soft dough.
Let set 30 minutes before using.

title: ranch dressing
directions: To make dip, use mayonnaise and sour cream plus spices.
Add crab or clams.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip the cheese in egg yolk, then flour/bread crumbs.
Heat olive oil until it smokes; add cheese.
Squeeze lemon juice on each slice.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Dissolve sugar in cream and boil to the thread test (228°), stirring occasionally.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook until syrup reaches soft ball test (236°).
Cool.
Beat until somewhat thickened but not until it loses its gloss.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a greased marble slab or double thickness of waxed paper.
The candy will flatten out into large cakes.
Makes 12 pralines.

title: cooled carrots
directions: Peel carrots; slice and boil in salted water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Boil other ingredients for 5 minutes and pour over carrots while hot.
When cold, refrigerate. These will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken with raspberry ginger sauce(serves 4)
directions: Heat butter with oil in large skillet or wok.
Add chicken and saute on all sides until golden.
Remove from skillet and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Drain excess fat and return to skillet to heat.
Deglaze pan by adding 3/4 cup raspberry vinegar. Return chicken to pan.
Add stock and simmer, covered, until chicken is tender and juices run clear with pricked with a fork. Transfer chicken to a serving
platter and keep warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers.
Chill 4 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into a 9x13 baking pan.
Dig several holes in dry ingredients.
In one hole put vanilla, in another vinegar and in another oil.
Then pour the water over everything. Mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture and stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Turn onto lightly floured bread board.
Knead for a minute or two (no rising is required).
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Brush with melted butter and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Make straws with pastry tube or shape in ball and flatten with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Will burn easily.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Blend in brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Take off stove.
Blend in confectioners sugar.
Good with spice or carrot cake.

title: ambrosia cream
directions: Drain pineapple. Peel and section oranges. Mix all together. Add a little honey. Garnish with a few orange sections. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: In an electric slow cooker, stir together all ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours (or on slow for 8 to 10 hours) or until beef is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, chocolate and flour together.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; stir.
Pour into precooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: creamy corn
directions: In a skillet combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt. Stir mixture over low heat until cheese melts. Add corn, heat through and serve. Garnish with parsley or a sprinkle of paprika.

title: strawberry-angel food dessert
directions: Cream
together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add a little milk if necessary.
Add Cool Whip and angel food cake. Spread
in a
9 x 13-inch pan and top with strawberries mixed with glaze. Chill; cut in squares.
Top with whipped topping.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Using electric mixer, whip the oil and sugar together for a minute.
Add eggs and beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
On low speed, mix in milk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and blend very gently until just mixed.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix together ingredients, but do not knead.
Roll out dough 1-inch thick.
Cut into rounds; brush tops with buttermilk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk, coconut, nuts (optional), powdered sugar and melted butter.
Roll in small balls.
Freeze and dip in chocolate chip mixture, which is chocolate chips and paraffin melted in double boiler.
It is best to dip in cool weather and to keep bonbons, cool immediately after dipping.
Use toothpicks to dip candy.

title: frozen whiskey sour
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: heavenly rice salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine the eggs, reserved syrup, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until mixture thickens.
Add to cooked rice.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Whip cream; fold the chilled rice along with the apples, marshmallows and reserved crushed pineapple.
Add coconut, nuts, cherries.

title: sweet coleslaw
directions: In a food processor, chop cabbage and carrots.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing and sugar to taste.
Mix well.
Makes real good coleslaw!

title: canned green beans
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil in a large pan.
Add green beans, cover with water and bring beans to a boil.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put beans in jars, cover with hot liquid and seal.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and 2/3 cup butter and pat into a 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Then add marshmallows and bake for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O with 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Put 1/2 of mixture into freezer for 30 minutes.
Add 8 ounces of sour cream to top of congealed mixture.
Add remaining 1/2 of mixture on top.
Congeal in refrigerator.

title: waldorf-yogurt salad
directions: Chop apple and thinly slice celery.
Halve the grapes.
Peel and slice the kiwi.
Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes; turn oven to 250 degrees and bake 15 additional minutes.
Pie is done when middle of pie does not move when shaken.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Stir in Cool Whip. Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan with one layer of graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers and pour remaining pudding mixture on top.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top.

title: butternut squash
directions: Divide squash lengthwise in half and place face down on foil. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes and scoop out shells.
Put in baking dish. Add brown sugar and butter to warm squash. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mini's mustard dip
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in bowl.
Cover.
Let sit overnight at room temperature.
Mix together sugar and egg and mustard mixture and cook in double boiler until it thickens. Cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Serve with ham, pretzels, cheese, etc.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in large jar or container and shake well. Very good on any salad.

title: chuck's confetti flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saute pan, place butter and olive oil.
Add green, yellow and red peppers, Vidalia onion and green onion tops.
Saute slowly.
Meanwhile, divide flounder fillets in 4 ramekin or au gratin dishes.
Sprinkle with pepper and garlic salt to taste.
When peppers and onions become almost soft, add mushrooms; continue to saute.
Place flounder ramekins in preheated oven for 5 minutes.
Remove flounder.
Fold crabmeat into saute mix.
Divide mix between 4 ramekins on top of flounder. Replace in oven another 7 minutes.
Remove; sprinkle with Parmesan and small amount of butter.
Place under broiler until slightly brown.
Serves 4.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook noodles (may be lasagna noodles or regular noodles). Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato soup and seasoning mix and simmer 10 minutes. Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, hamburger, noodles, cheese, soup, etc.; finish with hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Sift the flour and salt together; set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, bring water and butter to a boil.
Pour flour in all at once.
Reduce heat to very low and stir quickly until a soft ball is formed and mixture comes away from sides of pan, forming a compact mass of dough.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add 1 egg into dough and beat until smooth.
Add second egg and beat hard until batter is light and fluffy.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet if large puffs are desired or by teaspoon if smaller ones are desired.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 additional minutes.
Remove from oven; cool and slice in half.
Cut open.
(The puffs will be hollow.)
Fill with vanilla or chocolate custard.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, and cider.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth; add.
Slowly bring to boiling; simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.
Float clove-studded orange slices atop.
Serves 10.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute
green onions in margarine.
Add cooking wine and blend in	Cream
Sauce.
Add mushrooms and shrimp and blend in sour cream
(or	sour
cream and yogurt mixture).
Add parsley and thyme.
Serve over yellow rice.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: chicken soup
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove skin if desired.
Remove chicken and lightly brown onion.
Drain excess oil and replace chicken. Cover with water and cook in deep pot.
Add carrots, celery, scallions, parsley, garlic powder and pepper.
Add bouillon cubes and tomatoes.
Cook for 3 hours on low.
Remove chicken from bone; cut and place back in soup.
Cook tortellini and add to soup.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, salt and water, then egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked shell.

title: broccoli and artichoke heart salad
directions: Mash garlic with salt using a table fork.
This works well in a large wooden bowl.
Add olive oil; stir.
Add hot sauce; stir. Add Lea & Perrins; stir.
Add bitters; stir.
Add lime and lemon; stir.
Add vinegar; stir.
Parboil broccoli just enough to keep from being tough.
Put broccoli, artichoke hearts, chives and tomatoes into dressing and mix well.
Let set for at least one hour.

title: baked chicken with potatoes and carrots
directions: Cut up chicken; salt and pepper.
Put in greased baking dish and put in oven at 300° to 350°.
Then add potatoes, carrots, onion and garlic.
Mix golden onion soup mix in at least 1 cup of water in a pot, plus cream of celery or mushroom soup, plus 1/2 can of water.
Heat, then pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed using 1/4 water and 1/2 pineapple juice as liquid.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: homemade ice cream roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch Teflon jelly roll pan.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Mix other ingredients and bake about 1 hour in covered casserole.
A little more liquid may be added near end of baking if rice seems dry.
Bake at 300 to 325°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add blueberries.
Set aside.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir lightly.
Fill paper-lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Place vanilla wafers in each paper-lined cup of a muffin pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers, filling cups full.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Leave in pan and chill overnight.
Add pie filling for topping, if desired.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients at once. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 10 inch bundt pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes, until springy. Cool at least 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco oil and stir well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add carrots and mix.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans, about 25 minutes.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all in the blender.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan and pour ingredients into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until a knife inserted near middle comes out clear.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute in 2 tablespoons of oil the hamburger, garlic and onion until well done.
Add tomato sauce, enchilada sauce and soup. Simmer a short time.
Tear tortillas into small pieces.
Alternate a layer of meat sauce with tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Finish with meat and cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ginger's cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine milk and butter in a saucepan and scald.
Pour into a large bowl and add sugar and salt, stirring to completely dissolve sugar.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.

Add yeast water and egg to milk mixture, stirring well. Add 1 1/2 cups flour, stirring by hand for 3 to 4 minutes or mixing for 2 minutes with an electric mixer on low speed (mixture will be somewhat smooth).
Add 1/2 cup flour and stir in well. Continue adding flour, a little at a time, stirring well after each addition.
When dough is just a little sticky, flour hands well and turn dough out onto a floured surface.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat until stiff.
Add, if desired, coconut, pineapple or berries.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Heat to boiling point the butter, cocoa and coca cola.
Add to the flour and sugar mixture. Stir to blend and add buttermilk, soda, eggs, salt, and vanilla. Stir with a spoon until well blended.
Spoon in marshmallows and pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Batter will be thin, top with icing while hot.

title: open-face pizza sandwiches
directions: Brown meat.

Add other ingredients, except cheeses and cook, covered, for 10 minutes. Spread meat mixture on split muffins. Grate cheeses and sprinkle on top of meat. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. This is very good for a teenage party.
Yields 50.

title: bagna cauda
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients in heavy pot for about 8 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add pepper.
Serve warm with fresh vegetables: mushrooms, celery, cherry tomatoes, zucchini and crudites.
Keep warm in a small fondue pot.

title: chicken squares
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.

title: patio potato salad
directions: Cook milk, sugar, vinegar, 1 egg, mustard, butter, flour, salt and celery seed over low heat until thickened.
Then add mayonnaise, chopped onion and hard-cooked eggs.
Mix well and pour over cooked, diced potatoes.
May also be used as a coleslaw dressing.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit (save 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice).
Cut peaches in 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine fruit, maraschino cherries, marshmallows and ginger.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat pineapple juice to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Add orange and lemon juice, sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.
Chill mixture.

title: potato wedges
directions: Slice potatoes into wedges.
Melt butter; mix with Mrs.
Dash. Dip potatoes in mixture.
Lay potatoes out on pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Turn potatoes over; bake an additional 20 minutes. Cover with cheese.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, juice, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over cauliflower and onions.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Line large casserole dish with wafers and layer of bananas. Mix softened cream cheese real good with sugar and add to prepared Dream Whip; go by directions on package.
Layer on top of bananas. Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Pour blueberry pie filling on top.
Can also be used with cherries or fresh strawberries.

title: whole wheat machine made bread
directions: Measure all ingredients accurately into bread machine in order given. Select cycle. When done, remove baked bread from pan and cool. Makes 1 large loaf.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together and chill.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix until evenly moist.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then at 325° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: yummy shake
directions: You will need a blender, measuring cups, spoons and glasses.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; tear off bone.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, chicken broth and 2 eggs; pour into pan to bake.
Add Stove Top seasoned bread crumbs over mixture, then sprinkle season packet over bread crumbs.
Grate enough cheese to cover casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup milk over casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add consomme, catsup, mushrooms and garlic.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add flour and stir well. Reduce heat; add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown
the
chicken
in
the
oil until cooked, about 5 minutes.
Add
the broth, wine, broccoli and soup and bring to a boil.
Stir
in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Scald milk, pour over oats, sugar, shortening, raisins and salt; stir until dissolved and lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water, add to milk mixture, beat egg and add, then gradually add the flour and mix to a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board for 10 minutes or until smooth and satiny.
Shape into ball and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down on lightly floured board, divide dough, cover and let rise for 10 minutes.
Roll each portion into long rectangle.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon, sprinkle over dough.
Roll up crosswise to form loaves with edges of dough underneath, place in greased 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch pans. Brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 40 or 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter and jelly pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Spoon mixture into crust and chill.
Spread with preserves and top with whipped topping.

title: louisiana reindeer food(nonedible)
directions: Mix the box of oats with the glitter.
Sprinkle on sidewalk and front door steps.
The smell of the oats as well as the reflection of the glitter in the moon will make sure the reindeer stop at your house.

title: cupa cupa cupa
directions: In large bowl thoroughly mix all three ingredients.
Pour into ovensafe baking dish and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream to cut sweetness.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Grease a large heavy casserole.
Layer in this order: onions, potatoes, ground chuck, kidney beans, rice and celery.

title: chewy figs(heritage)
directions: Leave the stems on figs.
Place into a 6-quart pot with sugar and cloves.
Let stand overnight.
The next morning, pick up the pot and with a clockwise or counter clockwise movement, get the sugar to dissolve.
At this point do not stir with a spoon.
Place over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a slow boil and boil for 30 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Do this for 3 days, letting the figs stand in syrup between boilings.
At the end of the three boilings, pour into a sieve to drain.
Place figs on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Turn figs daily for 3 to 4 days. Store in small, tightly covered containers with waxed paper between each layer.
Refrigerate or freeze to keep from molding.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add the vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Mix well.
Sift into the flour, baking powder and baking soda; mix well.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Spoon half batter into a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over batter. Spoon in the remaining batter and sprinkle with more sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 1/2 hour before removing from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and roll in pecans.

title: round steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into 6 serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat.
Pound into both sides.
Brown meat in the oil in large frying pan.
Dissolve instant beef bouillon in hot water.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Melt butter in large pan.
Add rice, carrots, celery, green onions and thyme leaves.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove 1/2 cup liquid from meat, adding enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into rice mixture.
Cover tightly.
Cook 15 minutes (or until tender).
Place around steak on meat platter. May make gravy using juice from steak.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Divide crescent rolls into 4 squares. Lay on wax paper in the refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cover sauce top well with onion powder.
Half cover sauce top with garlic powder.
Pour in some white cooking wine.

title: raspberry spirals
directions: Beat butter in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Slowly beat in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Divide in 4 equal parts. Flatten into disks.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Melt butter in non-stick pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Add thinly sliced hot dogs.
Mix in partially-cooked potatoes, diced.
Add 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and grated cheese.

title: buttermilk donuts
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix together sugar, unbeaten eggs, buttermilk, sour cream, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir until light.
Combine flour and egg mixtures (may need more flour; dough needs to be stiff enough to roll out).
Roll 3/8-inch thick; cut with floured donut cutter.
Fry in deep fat (salad oil, shortening or lard) at 375° until golden brown.
Turn once.
Drain on paper.
While warm, roll in 1/2 cup granulated sugar.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add fruit and juice. Chill until set.
Fold in whipped cream, mayonnaise, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.
Top with grated cheese.

title: corn puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat shortening until sizzling. Drop by teaspoons into hot shortening in skillet.
Fry until browned.
Serve hot.

title: rice balls
directions: Cook rice.
Drain well at least 1 hour.
Mix grated cheese, pepper and egg yolks with rice until sticky.
Set aside.
Cube Mozzarella.
