Make a rice patty, place Mozzarella cube in center and place another rice patty on top.
Shape into a ball.
Beat egg whites.
Roll ball first in egg whites then in bread crumbs.
Set balls for 2 hours.
Fry in very hot oil.
Drain and serve hot.

title: ham and broccoli strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Then, using a glass, cut 12 bread rounds, saving remaining scraps of bread.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, fill bottom of pan with scraps of bread.
Add a layer of sliced American cheese.
Add all of broccoli (barely cooked) and your cubed ham.
Put bread rounds on top of ham.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash your bananas up real good with fork.
Pour in bowl and then add rest of ingredients.
Put in loaf pan, greased and floured, then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. You can add pecans if wished.

title: alpine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain and chop broccoli.
Layer one-half of the broccoli, ham and cheese in pastry shell.
Repeat.
Sprinkle onion over top and set aside.
Gradually stir milk into eggs; add seasonings.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Continue to bake for an additional 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven; let stand a few minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: julie's original
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped chicken.
Mix well.
Roll biscuits thin.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Fold over like tarts.
Make all 10 before putting into broth.
Mix broth and soup; bring to boil.
Put all pies in at once.
Let broth cover them and boil 5 minutes.
Take up with spatula and cover with gravy.
Makes 10.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all.
Serve with fresh raw carrots, celery, radishes, cauliflower, etc.
Yields 2 cups, serves 15.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Chill. Serve with melted chocolate on top.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Saute onion and garlic; add chili powder and cumin plus beans, chilies and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Remove from heat and mix in 1 cup of tortilla chips and 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour into a lightly buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread remaining tortilla chips around outer edge of baking dish.
Place sour cream in the center and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease round casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients, except 2 tablespoons onions.
Beat for 30 seconds. Spread into casserole dish.
Sprinkle onions on top and press into dough.
Bake for about an hour.
Cool upside down.

title: kraut ensemble
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Place layer of noodles in 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover with half raw kraut and half of the sausage patties.
Repeat.
Add 2 cups water and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover 10 minutes before serving.

title: flo's sinful cookies
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add ingredients by layers.
Save 1/2 cup chocolate chips for the top.
Pour Eagle Brand over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.
Cut into squares.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Mash potatoes
and
add relish, mustard and mayonnaise. Place potato mixture
in greased casserole dish.	Cut hot dogs in two, then
split
down
the middle.
Arrange upright around edges of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Combine beaten eggs with milk.
Sprinkle cheese over uncooked pie shell.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Layer 1/2 of broccoli, 1/2 of ham and 1/2 of egg mixture.
Layer the remaining half of ingredients.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: night before french toast
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange bread slices in one layer in bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients except butter.
When mixed thoroughly, pour over bread in pan.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Dot with the butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until bread is puffy and slightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix together with stuffing mix, egg, ketchup, onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange peppers in baking dish.
Stuff with beef mixture.
Pour 1 pint tomato juice over peppers.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Just before serving, place slices of American cheese on top.
Melt cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook first three ingredients together until it becomes a hard boil stage.
Then add butter and soda.
Pour over popped corn and shape into popcorn balls.

title: salted pecans
directions: Spread pecans in a baking pan.
Dot margarine slices over pecans.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully to prevent burning.
Stir several times to mix.

title: red rock candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan; cook over low heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly. Continue to cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until it reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Add cinnamon candies.
Continue cooking and stirring constantly until it reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine.
Quickly pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; cool.
Break into small pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: spinach - creamed
directions: Cook spinach with water just until thawed and completely separated.
Drain and discard water.
Add margarine.
Stir until melted, over medium heat.
Mix flour into sour cream.
Add to spinach and stir well, until bubbly.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Season and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon fluff dessert
directions: Place vanilla wafers, butter and white sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 to 3/4 cup Cool Whip on top of wafer mixture.
Add pie filling, then spread 8 ounces Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: spaghetti and cheese casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water; drain.
Combine ingredients. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until mixture doesn't jiggle. Don't brown the top as it makes the cheese tough.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs which have been beaten slightly.
Add cooled, melted butter.
Mix well. Add pecans, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes and top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream drizzled in chocolate.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together oleo, eggs, salt and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in blueberries.

title: peanut butter swirls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Beat in peanut butter, egg and milk.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Place dough on lightly floured waxed paper. Roll in 15 x 8 x 1/4-inch rectangle.
Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Cool slightly; spread over dough.
Roll like jelly roll, lifting waxed paper slightly with each turn.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° on ungreased sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Very sticky dough. Put in refrigerator overnight or freezer about 1 hour. Pat out dough and cut desired size. Bake at 300° until done.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion and green pepper until done.
Add spaghetti, sugar and cubed cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
This works well to put in crock-pot.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and rice into soup and water. Add meat.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. In last 5 to 10 minutes, sprinkle your favorite cheese on top. Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in
mixing
bowl.
Add
flour
and salt.
Mix well; add honey
and milk, making a thin, smooth batter.	Pour into pitcher and
allow	to
stand
for	30 minutes.
Peel and slice apples very thin; drizzle honey over them and toss until all apple slices are coated.

title: four layer surprise
directions: Mix butter, flour, sugar and nuts like pie dough. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In small bowl, combine softened cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Beat well, then add chocolate bits and stir well. Set aside.
In another bowl combine dry ingredients, then add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well until blended.
Fill 18 paper-lined muffin tins 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top with teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with extra sugar, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: club car dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
(May use blender.)
Chill. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: juicy beef brisket
directions: Place frozen brisket (fat side up) in 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry soup mix, garlic, salt and pepper over top of brisket.
Add water to cover bottom of pan about 1/2 to 1-inch. Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Put in 250° oven.
Bake at least 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes (use broth from brisket or make gravy from broth).
Tender and juicy.
Plan to start early in the day.

title: tiropetes(cheese pies)
directions: Mash cheeses together; add parsley, eggs and pepper and mix well.
Cut phyllo into strips, about 2 x 12-inches.
Keep phyllo covered with damp cloth until ready to use.
Brush phyllo strips with butter.
Place 1 teaspoon cheese mix on 1 corner.
Fold corner over mix to form a triangle.
Continue folding corners over until phyllo is all folded in.
Place triangles on buttered baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: caramel squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg until crumbly.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Mix condensed milk, egg, brickle bits, pecans and vanilla.
Place on crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares when set.

title: grits casserole
directions: Beat yellows and fold into grits.
Beat egg whites and fold into grits.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: natalie's eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip slices in egg; coat slices with Italian seasoned breadcrumbs.
Fry slices in skillet with oil until lightly browned; remove slices from skillet and place on side.
Mix together tomato/spaghetti sauce and 1 cup of water.
Alternate layers in skillet, one layer of eggplant, then layer of sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts and some of the liquid evaporates.
Serve warm with salad and Italian bread.
Enjoy!

title: john jones bean soup
directions: Mix soup and half and half in pot.
Heat to boiling point, but do not allow to boil.
Stir thoroughly.
Delicious with a green salad and your favorite grilled cheese sandwich.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Heat beans in liquid.
Let cook slowly for about 10 minutes. Mix beans with soup, leaving about half the liquid in the beans. Put in buttered casserole.
Place in 300° oven for 20 minutes. Add onion rings.
Leave in oven just long enough to crisp onions.

title: meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Scoop batter onto a spoon and rake it against the bowl.
Push batter off of spoon witn finger to make pretty shape.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: firecracker punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, pineapple juice, sugar and almond extract in pitcher.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill in refrigerator.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: shirley's boston brown bread
directions: Boil water and raisins for 2 minutes and let cool.
When cooled, mix it with all the other ingredients.
Pour batter into a bread pan or into (2/3 full) well-greased muffin tin cans (use corn, vegetable cans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Spread half of vanilla wafers in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spread on top of vanilla wafers.
Add strawberries.
Add remaining wafers.
Spread with whipped cream and chill until firm.

title: white chocolate crunch
directions: Mix together and spread on 10 x 15-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
Break up.

title: bran rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over first four ingredients and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add eggs and yeast which has been dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Gradually beat in flour and mix well.
Put in refrigerator and use as needed.
Form into rolls and let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Fry sausage or hamburger.
Mix Jiffy corn bread, egg, milk and cream-style corn.
Add whole kernel corn to taste.
Spread thin layer on bottom of greased cake pan.
Add a layer of sausage or hamburger.
Add layer of Mozzarella cheese (2 cups).
Cover entirely with rest of the corn bread mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Top with butter.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave dish.
Cover; cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook an additional 4 to 6 minutes, or until mixture comes to full boil.

title: honey glazed party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels and pecans.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a small pan.
Stir in honey; blend well. Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly glazed. Spread on wax paper.
Cool completely.
Put in airtight container.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Combine and mix ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart Pyrex pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat in iron skillet; drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream.
Pour half of the batter into a greased pan.
Sprinkle half of the topping (first mixture) on the batter.
Pour remaining batter and rest of the topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hen until tender; save chicken stock. Debone and dice chicken. Cook and drain spaghetti. Fry onion, pepper and pimento in bacon drippings until tender, but not brown. Then add chicken and other seasonings.
Add undiluted soup and add spaghetti. Let simmer until thick. If too dry, add chicken stock. Add grated cheese and stir. Save some for top or mix all and bake in an oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: bacon chestnut roll ups
directions: Wrap each chestnut with half slice bacon and secure with a round toothpick.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350° on broiler pan. Remove from oven and drain fat.
Make sauce from brown sugar, chili sauce and mayonnaise.
Dip baked roll-ups in sauce and return to oven for 20 minutes.
Yields about 40 roll-ups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: red pepper and white bean soup(serves 6)
directions: Mix butter and olive oil in saucepan.
Add sliced peppers and onion.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes until soft (do not let brown).
Add entire can of beans, including liquid.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into a food processor and process until smooth.
Pour through a strainer, pushing the mixture with the back of a spoon to get out all the liquid.
There should be 3 cups.
Recipe can be made ahead to this point.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan and line with wax paper.
Pour batter in pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, pudding, eggs, 3/4 cup peach Schnapps, 1/2 cup orange juice and orange extract; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix at least 8 hours before baking.
Place first 3 ingredients in large cake pan or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine flour and mustard; sprinkle over bread mixture.
Beat eggs, margarine and milk together.
Pour over bread, cheese and meat mixture. Refrigerate 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
This is a good breakfast dish for company.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup, vegetables, chicken and milk together.
Pour into pie shell.
Put another pie shell on top.
Press edges together. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: rum cake
directions: Cook in a tube pan at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: refreshing drink
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add all other ingredients.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds.

title: chicken spaghetti and sauce
directions: Saute green pepper, onion, celery and garlic in oleo, then add 1 cup chicken broth and simmer 1 hour.

title: no-bake lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar in small bowl. Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan, reserving 2 tablespoons for top.
Combine gelatin, 1/2 cup of the sugar and egg yolks in medium saucepan.
Beat with rotary beater until well mixed.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar and gelatin are dissolved and mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Press cheese through sieve or food mill into a large bowl.
Stir in cooled gelatin mixture, lemon rind and juice.
Beat egg whites until foamy in a small bowl.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine; add roux.
Mix thoroughly.
Add tomato paste and mix well, cooking 5 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can water.
Heat and add more water if too thick (remember the crawfish will create water also.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes at a slow simmer.
Add crawfish tails. Simmer about 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not boil.
Add ketchup and lemon juice and simmer.
Adjust Creole seasoning to taste while simmering about 20 minutes.
Cooking time approximately 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: florentine baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick skins with a fork.
Bake potatoes in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
While potatoes are still hot, cut slice from top of each and scoop out center, taking care not to break skin.

title: best biscuits
directions: Sliver margarine into flour in large bowl.
Add milk and stir with fork.
Push dough to 1 side of bowl, flour bowl.
Scrape dough to floured side and flour other side.
Mix; knead in bowl 12 times.
Pinch of small piece of dough and shape into biscuits (with floured hands).
Bake on cookie sheet in 450° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Add oil
to 14-inch Dutch oven.
Put over coals and add diced chicken.
Stir-fry	until
cooked.	Add
green peppers. When cooked add 1 gallon of water.
Bring to a boil and remove from fire.
Add soup packages (crush noodles in packet before adding). Let stand for 3 minutes and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two loaf pans.
Beat eggs and then add vanilla, oil and sugar.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pans and bake for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Roll dough, cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Place wafer in mini cupcake papers.
Fill with mixture and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: creamy noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Cream butter and cream cheese together; add salt, sugar and eggs.
Add milk gradually and blend well; stir in noodles.
Mixture will be runny. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: red and green pepper salad
directions: Whisk vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning together. Do in large bowl.
Core and cut peppers into strips.
Slice and separate onion.
Mix all together in bowl.
Toss and cover. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, green peppers, celery and garlic in oleo (do not brown).
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients together; add remaining ingredients.
Cook in large casserole dishes at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with strawberries, bananas (dipped in lemon juice), fresh pineapple and grapes.

title: bonnie's rolls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add milk, yeast, potatoes, then eggs.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.

title: potato corn bake
directions: Save 1 tablespoon bacon grease, saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Stir in milk, corn, margarine, salt and pepper. Cook on medium heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in potato flakes and sour cream.
Blend well.
Spoon into greased pan, top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake on 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable burgers
directions: In a blender, finely chop celery, onion, scallion and garlic or finely dice them by hand.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine barley, chickpeas, oatmeal, salt, paprika, basil, soy sauce and pepper.
Mix them thoroughly with a wooden spoon or with your hands.
Add the chopped onion, celery, scallion and garlic to the barley mixture and mix again.
Shape into six burgers.
Heat olive oil in a nonstick skillet.
Add burgers and brown 5 to 7 minutes on each side or bake the patties at 350° on a lightly oiled cookie sheet for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 patties.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and add all other ingredients; simmer about an hour.
Good cold or reheated.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs with corn and add to dry ingredients.
Heat shortening in skillet (1/2-inch deep).
When shortening is hot, drop corn mixture from a tablespoon into fat.
Brown completely. Can be kept hot in oven, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper and put in refrigerator for two hours. Saute grated onion in 3 tablespoons butter. Add beef and cook quickly. Set aside. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add 1 tablespoon flour. Stir and add beef stock. Cook until thick. Boil for 2 minutes. Add sour cream alternately with tomato paste. Stir constantly and do not boil. Add beef and heat a few minutes. Serve with noodles.

title: canapes
directions: Heat leeks and butter in pot.
Add onion and garlic and saute a few minutes.
Add wine and cook until liquid is gone.
Add nutmeg. Slice thinly 2 ounces Italian bread.
(Any party breads or French can be used.)
Bake on cookie sheet at 425°, finely spread mix on top.
Sprinkle cheese (Mozzarella, Cheddar, etc.).
Pop back in oven until melted.
Excellent addition with soups.

title: feta cheese and shrimp
directions: Cook onion in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, wine, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Bring liquid to boil; turn down to simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove from stove; cool down and stir in shrimp.
Spoon into buttered gratin dish and sprinkle with Feta cheese.
Place in 450° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and shrimp are pink.
Serve over pasta.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook meat in oil until brown with onions and celery.
Add tomatoes, season with salt, pepper and a little bit of sugar. Cook until all vegetables are tender.
Meanwhile, cook and drain macaroni.
Mix with vegetables.
Put in casserole, cover with Velveeta cheese.
Makes 1 (2-quart) casserole.
Bake until brown on top (approximately 1 hour).

title: green tomato mincemeat(splendid way to salvage green tomatoes)
directions: Core and quarter tomatoes and apples; put through food chopper with raisins.
Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring frequently.
Pack at once in hot pint jars. Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 25 minutes.

title: dannon brownies(makes 24 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Combine brownie mix, yogurt, egg whites or egg substitute and vanilla in bowl. Mix well.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in pan.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 22 to 24 minutes or 32 to 34 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: date krispies
directions: In large bowl, combine Rice Krispies and pecans.
In skillet, combine butter, sugar, dates and eggs.
Cook seven minutes slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour over Rice Krispies and pecan mixture and mix.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in coconut if desired.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Butter hands when rolling out to prevent sticking to hands.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cheese, flour and sugar. Pour over pineapple. Sprinkle crackers on top and add melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: walnut cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder, and salt.
Set aside.

title: raisin casserole bread("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased one-quart casseroles and smooth tops.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Loosen edges and turn out onto racks to cool.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crab meat.
Mix well.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook cakes in oil.
Brown about 5 minutes on each side.

title: no-fat chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, stir together unsweetened cocoa powder, cornstarch, milk and sugar.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter together and line bottom and sides of layer pan or Pyrex bowl.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on high speed about 2 minutes after each addition. Add lemon, vanilla, and almond extracts and beat
Add soda to flour.	Then add sour cream and flour alternately.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn cake onto cooling rack as soon as you take it from oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients to the combined butter and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in an uncooked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: thanksgiving day salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and cranberry sauce.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in mold.
Refrigerate. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: brisket
directions: Put brisket, meat side down, in marinade overnight. Refrigerate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and molasses.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients together and add to soft mixture.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: whiz cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll dough around on cloth-covered board lightly dusted with Bisquick to prevent sticking.
Knead 8 to 10 times to smooth dough.
Add more Bisquick if too wet or sticky.
Roll in 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spread with soft butter. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll; seal well.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 300°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: egg roll
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok to 275°.
Stir-fry ginger and scallion 1 minute or until aroma comes.
Add pork.
Stir-fry at 350° for 1 minute until color changes.
Add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and sugar.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove.
Mix shrimp with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch.
Stir-fry quickly at 350°.
Add sherry.
Stir-fry 30 seconds.
Remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok to 375°.
Stir-fry cabbage, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and celery 1 minute.
Remove.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok to 375°.
Stir-fry bean sprouts 1 minute.
Remove.
Combine pork, shrimp and vegetables in wok.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Stir-fry at 375° until thoroughly heated. Remove to colander.
Drain liquid.
Cool mixture.
Set aside; ready to be used as a filling.

title: holly punch(low-calorie)
directions: Combine water and lime juice.
Add well chilled low-calorie beverage and sparkling water.
Add a few drops of mint extract, green food color and non-calorie sweetener to taste.
Float ice cubes made with green food coloring.

title: *savory eggs
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with cheese slices.
Top cheese with dots of butter.
Mix together the half and half, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour half of this mixture over the cheese in the baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly; add chives and pour in baking dish.
Add remaining cream mixture; top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: smoked sausage chowder
directions: Cut sausage into bite sized pieces and brown in stew pot. Add beans, tomatoes, onion, green pepper and potatoes.
Cover with water and season to taste.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for one hour or until potatoes are tender.
If thicker soup is desired, add tablespoons of instant mashed potatoes until desired consistency.

title: maple-pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine oats and milk; let stand 5 minutes. Add eggs, pumpkin, maple syrup and oil; stir well. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Add oat mixture to dry ingredients, lightly stirring. For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup batter onto a hot skillet, coated with cooking spray.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked. Yields 16 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and pumpkin, beat in mixer until blended together, but do not over beat.
Fill 3 greased and floured pans about half full.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water. Add margarine and cover pan. Set aside dry ingredients. Mix sugars and eggs in large bowl. Add dry ingredients to mixture and stir well. Add oatmeal mixture and stir well. Pour mix into 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and pineapple.
Blend in half the nuts and remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into a ball using wax paper.
Chill.
Roll in remaining nuts to coat outside. Refrigerate for flavors to blend.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda. Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease pan and coat with cornmeal. Brown in pan in oven.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Line pan with cornflake crumbs. Cook broccoli and strain all water.
Take potato masher and mash broccoli. Add eggs, flour, onion soup mix and mayonnaise to broccoli.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle cornflake crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 425° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon meringue pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Bake pie crust as label directs.

In saucepan, stir cornstarch, salt, and sugar. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, lemon peel and juices; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until lemon mixture is thickened and boils; remove from heat.

title: elegant puffed broccoli
directions: Arrange hot cooked broccoli in shallow 1 1/2-quart pan or broilerproof serving dish.
In a small bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and salt until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cheese and mayo; spoon evenly over hot broccoli.
Broil 6 inches from source of heat for 4 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve immediately.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger.
Add seasoning mix and refried beans.
Mix well.
Spread in bottom of 10 x 13 pan.
Spread sour cream on top of meat mixture.
Shred lettuce; put on top of this sour cream. Add cheese and olives.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread in layers the pineapple and blueberries.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar on blueberries, then dry yellow cake mix, then melted butter or margarine. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Cook at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown on top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix cake, pudding, oil, water and eggs at highest speed for 8 minutes.
Add butter flavoring during the last minute of beating.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream oleo on high speed of mixer.
Add sugars gradually and mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients on low speed.
Fold in nuts and M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.
Chocolate chips may be used instead of M&M's.

title: sugar crust cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add flavoring, salt and sifted flour. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: orange chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour mixture and pan-fry in margarine in 2-inch skillet over medium heat, until lightly browned on both sides (adding more margarine as needed).
Remove chicken.

Reduce heat and add any leftover flour mixture, 1/2 cup chicken broth and 1/2 cup orange marmalade or more according to taste, to skillet. Return chicken to skillet and simmer for 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: sweetened condensed milk(like eagle brand)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and beat until smooth.
Equal to 1 1/2 cups (or 14 ounces).
Will be consistency of honey.

title: texas cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and green peppers and cook until tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except cornbread mix and paprika.
Place the meat mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Prepare cornbread mix as directed on package and spread onto the meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: baked corn with sour cream
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cook onion in margarine; blend in flour and salt.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring until smooth. Bring to a boil; add corn.
Cook until heated throughout.
Fold in half of bacon and pimento; pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with parsley and remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding.
Blend until creamy the cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool whip and prepared pudding.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large kettle; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook until done.
More juice may be used if needed.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Cook mixture of sugar, egg, margarine, dates and nuts for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut.
(You may grease hands with butter to prevent mixture from sticking to your hands.)

title: fried noodles
directions: Drop noodles in boiling water.
Boil one minute. Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: cooked breakfast cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar on bottom of well-greased 9-inch round pan. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Pour topping over nuts.
Dip biscuits in margarine and arrange in pan with 15 overlapping around edge (laying flat, not up side of pan) and then final 5 in center. Bake at 400° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Add to melted oleo and sugar and use as crust.
Save 1/2 cup to sprinkle over top.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cut butter into sugar; add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts.
Combine with first mixture.
Stir in apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: fried chicken
directions: Pour 1/2 inch cooking oil in pan and heat until hot.
Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Place in oil and keep turning until both sides are brown.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, margarine and sour cream. Add rest of ingredients. Pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add two packages of jello.
Fold in strawberries, nuts, pineapple and mashed bananas.
Mix together well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Ready to serve in a few hours.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Place brisket, fat side up, in a large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove beef and slice thinly.
Arrange in loaf cake pan or roaster.
Remove fat from gravy and pour over beef.
Cover tightly and heat at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter rice krispy squares
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, and salt.
Bring to a full boil. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, chocolate chips, and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Mix in cereal.
Press in buttered 9-inch x 13-inch pan and cut into squares.

title: maple custard pie
directions: In top of double boiler, stir together the syrup, egg yolks, milk and flour.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter.
Cool. Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff for meringue. Gradually add sugar.
Pour custard mixture in pie shell.
Cover with the meringue.
Bake until meringue is lightly browned, approximately 12 minutes.

title: pat's salad
directions: Mix sour cream, Hidden Valley Ranch mix and mayonnaise.
Add the cauliflower, carrots and broccoli.
Let set for 6 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add next 6 items and beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured angel food cake pan for 2 hours at 300°.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: joan's hearty hot dish
directions: Cook onions, carrots and celery in salted water.
Add hamburger, lima beans, tomatoes, catsup, vinegar, mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: quick cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in closed container.
Put 2 teaspoons heaping mixture to 1 cup hot water.
Mix as needed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil and grated zucchini.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Then add to the first mixture.
Bake in 2 oiled loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.
Tasty!

title: pork roast
directions: Rub roast with both salts and pepper.
Marinate in remaining ingredients overnight.
Bake at 300° slow oven for 2 1/2 hours depending on size of roast.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; cut into small pieces. Break broccoli into flowerets; boil until tender.
Put chicken in a
lightly greased casserole dish. Arrange broccoli over chicken. Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice; add soup.
Pour mixture over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over according to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken-rice casserole(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot slow cooker.
Cook 4 hours on low or until rice is done.

title: mama's melt in your mouth southern pie(this will make you famous.)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar. Beat until thick. Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well. Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm. Cool. Garnish with sweetened whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in skillet with oil about 24 minutes. Add onions and garlic last few minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add to meat. Cover and simmer until meat is almost tender, about 20 to 25 minutes. Add tomatoes and green pepper and cook 10 minutes longer.
